title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, chili beans and green chilies. Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer with tortillas, meat mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: white sauce
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill remaining sauce in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk. Add sour cream.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Put strawberries on bottom of pie crust, covering entire bottom. Add pudding mixture. Top with strawberry halves around edge. Chill in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine Cheddar, softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Chill mixture to make more firm.
Separate mixture in half.
Form each half into a ball.
Roll balls in chopped nuts (pecans or walnuts).

title: no-fat unfried french fries
directions: Slice potatoes in thin chips or julienne in traditional style. Mix egg whites, milk, flour and spices in bowl.
Dip potatoes in mixture and place on cookie sheet coated with vegetable cooking spray (Pam).
Spray top of potatoes lightly also.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: lil smokies and beans
directions: Saute green
pepper
and
onion in butter until tender. Mix with remaining
ingredients
and cook in oven on low until ready to serve.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over cole slaw mix. Marinate about one hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cut up Velveeta cheese into small squares.
Cook milk, cheese, flour and butter in saucepan on low heat until cheese melts.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Pour macaroni in baking dish.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni.
Top with Cheddar cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: cole slaw
directions: Blend vinegar, sugar, salad oil and salt well. Toss all remaining ingredients together lightly.
Chill several hours before serving.
May be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Combine soups and enchilada sauce.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons of sauce mixture into bottom of casserole dish.
Layer 1/2 of the tortillas, 1/2 of beef or chicken (or both), 1/2 chopped onion, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Cover; bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: no calorie dressing(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pint jar and cover tightly. Shake vigorously and store in refrigerator.
Shake before using. Makes 8 to 16 servings.
Yields 1 cup.
One serving:
1 to 2 tablespoons.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix flour, milk, margarine and black pepper.
Spoon over chicken mixture (this makes the crust).
Cook 30 minutes at 425°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line baking dish with Doritos.
Mix together and pour in other ingredients.
Crumble Doritos over top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This is a warm and filling dish to serve after a day of skiing!

title: indian cornbread
directions: Shred 1 pound (2 cups) Cheddar cheese.
Set aside.
Chop 1 medium onion and bell pepper.
Set aside.
Brown 1 pound ground meat in an iron skillet; empty all meat and grease out of skillet. Mix in a mixing bowl:
1 c cornmeal, 1 (16 oz) can creamed corn, 1 c milk, 1 egg, 1 tsp baking powder, and 1/4 tsp soda.
Pour 1/3 meal mixture into skillet.
Put meat, onions, pepper, then cheese, being careful not to let cheese touch sides.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool in pan 10 - 15 minutes for cheese to set before cutting.
Then cut in pan, or turn out on plate.

title: grandma maude's cornbread
directions: Stir flour, corn meal, baking soda and baking powder until mixed well.
Add buttermilk, egg and oil.
Mix well.
Put into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 500° until golden brown.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix together butter and sugar; stir in flour.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Chill dough.
Roll out.
Cut into squares; prick squares with fork.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
The tops do not brown during baking, nor does shape of cookies change.
Sprinkle granulated sugar on cookies after baking.
Cool and store in airtight container. Yields 2 dozen 1- inch to 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: scalloped potatoes and cheese
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Place into heavy saucepan with the water and salt.
Cover tightly.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: cheesy zucchini lasagne
directions: Mix chicken meat in with all of ingredients.
Add sage to season.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: old fashion bread dressing
directions: Buns should be dry (leave out overnight crumbled in large bowl).
Melt oleo, add onion and celery.
Slowly saute until tender (15 minutes).
Add to buns along with salt, pepper and sage.
(I like to put turkey broth over the top before baking.) Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Prepare peppers.
Place in casserole dish.
Cook rice, water and salt according to package directions.
Prepare rice and ground meat.
Mix together and add soup.

Mix ingredients thoroughly. Place rice-meat-soup mixture inside and around the peppers (use tops of pepper for decoration or the look of a whole pepper.) Cook in covered casserole for at least 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook milk, sugar, butter and syrup to a soft ball.
Add dates. Cook a little harder.
Beat until the mixture is creamy.
Add nuts.
Wet hands and make 2 rolls.
Roll in wax paper.
Cut in rounds.

title: pizza pasta casserole
directions: Mix ground beef, sauce, pasta and pepperoni.
Place in 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased casseroles.
Top each casserole with 2 cups Mozzarella cheese.
Freeze or bake at 350° till warm, about 35 minutes. Serves 18.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Stir well.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Stir and let congeal overnight.

title: jerry's fudge brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and oleo.
Stir in egg.
Add salt, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken on low heat until tender. Let cool and reserve broth. Debone and cut chicken into pieces. Saute pepper and onions in oleo on low heat 4 to 5 minutes. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth adding water if necessary; do not drain. Add cheese to hot spaghetti and stir until cheese is melted. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and place in casserole. Heat in oven until hot throughout. Makes large casserole. Can be cut in half for a small family. Also, may substitute tuna for the chicken if desired.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, mix egg, beer, salt, garlic and bread until soft. Add and mix thoroughly, venison, sausage and veggies.
Shape into something and place in center of cooking dish.
Cover with catsup. Put butter on potatoes and place around meat loaf.
Cover and cook at medium-low for 4 to 5 hours.
Enjoy!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove meat from bones and cut in chunks.
Cook potatoes, onions and carrots until tender.
Drain; add peas and set aside.
In a small saucepan, melt butter and add flour, stirring until smooth.
Add chicken broth and cream.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In a casserole dish,
place alternately layers of onions and potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt.
Spread
half
soup over and add water.
Place chops on
top
and
spread
remaining soup on top. Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° until chops are tender.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix water, yeast and honey and let stand 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix flour and blueberries together, coating the berries with flour.
Stir into liquid mixture.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill 3/4 full with batter.
Let rise 10 to 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: layered taco dip
directions: *I prefer to use 1 package Fiesta Ranch style dip if I can find it.

title: bettie's potato gnocchi
directions: Bring to boil the water, oil and salt.	Remove from heat.
Stir in potatoes.
Cool slightly.
Stir in egg yolks and enough flour to make a dough stiff enough to handle.
Divide in fourths on lightly floured surface.
Roll each fourth into a rope 3/4-inch in diameter.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Press each lightly with tines of fork.
Drop 1/4 of gnocchi at a time into boiling salted water. Simmer about 5 minutes or until they float to the surface.	With slotted spoon, remove to serving dish.
Keep warm.	Pour hot tomato sauce over gnocchi.
Serve with Parmesan.

title: raspberry-walnut shortbread bars
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and granulated sugar in medium bowl. Cut margarine into mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs. Press into bottom of lightly greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until edges are lightly golden.
Remove from oven; spread raspberry jam over shortbread.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour, salt and soda; add to egg mixture and blend. Stir in walnuts.
Spoon over jam, spreading lightly to corners of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes more or until top is set. Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Yield: 2 dozen bars.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In medium saucepan melt butter; stir in sugar, then crumbs, reserving 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken montego
directions: Mix flour and seasoning; roll chicken in this mixture.
Brown in shortening; remove from pan.
While chicken is browning, cook spaghetti.
Brown the mushrooms in the skillet in which the chicken was browned.
Add soup and marjoram and stir until smooth; add sour cream.
Put spaghetti in a shallow casserole; add peas and half the soup mixture; mix lightly.
Place chicken breasts on top and cover with the remaining soup mixture.
Cover and bake.

title: bulls eye
directions: Blend cheese and butter until fluffy.
Add Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Stir in flour and mix to form a dough.
Use 1 teaspoon of dough per olive and shape it around outside of olive. Chill several hours.
Bake at 400°
for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add to noodles. Add tomato sauce and olives and mix.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, oil, eggs, sour cream and water. Pour into
x
13-inch
greased
pan.
Top with brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Swirl Topping into cake.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: In a heavy saucepan or double boiler, combine sugar, egg whites, water and cream of tartar.
With a portable mixer, beat mixture on low speed for 1 minute.
Continue beating on low speed over low heat until frosting reaches 160°, about 8 to 10 minutes. Pour into a large mixing bowl; add vanilla.
Beat on high speed until frosting forms stiff peaks.
Makes approximately 7 cups.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast into 3/4 cup warm water.
Stir in 2 2/3 cups warm water, sugar, salt, shortening and 5 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board, knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 hour.
(Dough is ready if impression remains.)

title: sausage and kraut
directions: In a 6-quart crock-pot, rub inside with oleo or butter.
Drain kraut.
Cut the sausage into pieces. Stir occasionally. Cook 6 to 9 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan. Arrange slices of pineapple and cherries on sugar mixture.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes for topping to set.
Then turn upside-down onto cookie sheet.

title: rice crispies cookies(eggless)
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.

title: luscious lemon cake
directions: Beat egg yolks at high speed 4 minutes until thick and pale. Set aside.
Beat butter at medium speed until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Add combined flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in lemon rind, juice and vanilla.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: shortbread stix
directions: Press mixture into 13 x 9 pan. Prick many places with fork. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cut into sticks after baked.

title: mom's nut rolls
directions: Scald milk in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add crisco and sugar to hot milk.
Add warm water.
Stir well.
Let cool.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except for pecans.
Roll the mixture in the chopped pecans.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, using 2 cups Rice Chex. Reserve 1/2 cup Rice Chex for topping.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan
and
freeze.
Soften
vanilla ice cream. Spread over
crust. Freeze.
Pour
chocolate
syrup
on
ice
cream. Sprinkle remaining Rice Chex on top and freeze.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, butter and 1/3 cup sugar.
Butter sides and bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Press crumb mixture evenly onto bottom of pan.
Melt chocolate over hot, but not boiling water.
Stir until smooth.
Beat cream cheese until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, to cream cheese.
Gradually add 3/4 cup of sugar, mixing well, until blended.
Add melted chocolate, instant coffee and salt.
Stir until blended.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare cornbread and add green chilies to batter, bake according to package directions. Make ranch dressing with dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; set aside. Layer lettuce, crumbled cornbread, beans, bell pepper, corn, bacon and green onion in a large bowl. Repeat layers. Top with cheese and tomatoes. Serve with ranch dressing.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon; when done, add peas and onions.
Saute 1 minute. Add egg, scrambled.
When done, add rice.
Mix well.
Add soy sauce to season (as desired).

title: easy corn pudding
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in stick of margarine.
Stir to cook until onions start to turn clear.
Tear bread into small cubes, remove skillet from heat.
Add bread cubes and stir until all margarine is absorbed.
Add cream-style corn.
Sprinkle with sage.
Stir until all ingredients are mixed together.
Pour into medium-size greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until top starts to brown, 30 to 40 minutes.
Excellent with pork or chicken.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion together. Drain.

Pour into a big pot and add the tomato juice. Fill the tomato juice can 1/2 full with water and add to the pot. Add the vinegar, sugar and chili powder. Add the bay leaf and simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Add the spaghetti and chili beans.
Cook until the spaghetti is done.

title: brasato(italian beef roll)
directions: Strip sausage from links, brown and drain.
In a large bowl, mix sausage with eggs, cheeses and ham. Add oregano and basil. Heat sauce on low.
Trim most of the fat from the steak; with meat mallet, pound meat to 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle and pat pepper and garlic on it.
Spread the cheese/meat mixture evenly over steak, then roll up (jelly roll style) tightly.
Secure with household string on sides and lengthwise.
Brown all sides in olive oil. Transfer to red sauce and bring to a light boil, then simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, turning meat occasionally.
At about the last hour, add wine.
Cook pasta al dente. Top each serving with a slice of meat roll.
Serve with sauce and grated Parmesan or Romano cheese. (A fresh green salad, Italian bread with garlic butter and good dry, red wine go quite well.) Serves 8 to 10.
Great as leftovers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; add egg and mix well. Sift together flour, soda and salt, then add to sugar mixture alternately with the sour milk.
Add nuts last and stir just to mix, then pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: coffee cake (quick)
directions: Enough sweet milk to make a dough.
Mix and spread in pan greased with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes.
Turn upside-down and serve while hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
When done, pour off fat.
Top with catsup, brown sugar and mustard mixed together.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: whole grain pan rolls
directions: Combine water, honey and butter in a small saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Cool to 120°.
Combine wheat flour, oats, yeast and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Gradually add hot liquid mixture, beating at low speed with an electric mixer 1 minute.
Add egg and beat an additional 2 minutes at medium speed. Gradually add all-purpose flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a heavily floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 minutes).
Shape dough into 24 balls; place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix steak, flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in hot shortening. Add onion, mushrooms, garlic, sour cream, soup, sauces and green pepper to meat.
Stir.
Cover and cook on high until it steams. Simmer 20 to 40 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Sprinkle Parmesan over top.

title: coffee bars
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix the first 9 ingredients and place in pan. Top with the chocolate bits and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix together, let chill.

title: company rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions and saute until tender but not browned.
Combine onion, cheese, rice, mushrooms, consomme and almonds in 4 to 5-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken strips in garlic butter
directions: Flour chicken strips; season with salt and pepper and pan-fry in a small amount of oil until golden.
Combine broth, butter, garlic powder and parsley in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts and garlic dissolves.
Pour over chicken strips in frypan and cook slowly until broth thickens slightly (about 30 to 45 minutes). Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Rub garlic into meat and cut into 1/4-inch thick strips.
Mix next 4 ingredients and coat meat.
Brown well in small amount of oil.
Add onions and cook until translucent.
Add rest of flour mixture, consomme, water and mushrooms.
Cover and cook slow about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove cover and cook until thickened.
Add sour cream and chives.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, blending well. Serve with party rye or crackers.

title: hot chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chocolate over a low flame.
Pour in hot water gradually. Stir well.
Add butter.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add vanilla and salt.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef, garlic and onions.
Drain well.
Mash potatoes.
Heat green beans.
Stir hamburger, green beans and tomato sauce in bottom of pan.
Arrange mashed potatoes on top of hamburger mixture, and top with cheese (grated).
Put in oven until cheese melts.
Serve with salad.
Good, quick dinner. Service for 2.

title: peanut butter-fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough evenly into an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool 5 minutes. Spread gently with cream cheese and sprinkle with fruit mix, marshmallows and coconut.
Bake 8 additional minutes or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: lemon chess pies
directions: Place in half cooked pastry shell.
Bake at 375° until firm.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes, or until browned.

title: punch recipe
directions: If you use fresh lemon, add sugar.

title: bechamel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat, stirring, until cheese is melted.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: onion soup
directions: Place onions in blender, cover with water.
Blend on high until you have 4 cups.
Saute onion mix until golden brown. Cover with beef bouillon and water.
Add pepper and simmer covered for 30 minutes

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Dice eggs.
Cook and crumble bacon. Chop onion.
Dice celery.
Cook celery and onion in 3 tablespoons bacon drippings until tender.
Add flour, sugar, water, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add sauce to potato mixture.
Serve warm.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown crumbled sausage in heavy skillet and drain on paper towels.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate covered overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat and add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with corn chips if desired.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cream cheese, bacon, onion and pepper in bowl. Separate crescent rolls into two rectangles; place on 13 x 9 inch cutting board. Pinch seams together. Spread cheese mixture on each rectangle. Roll up, starting at longest side, and seal. Cut each roll into 16 slices. Place slices cut side down on flat baking stone. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: rio lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine oatmeal, flour, baking powder and sugar. Combine eggs and margarine.
Mix with oatmeal mixture. Add vanilla, lemon extract, almond extract and pecans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: five-flavor pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, oil and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until lemon colored.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add this alternately with milk.
Stir in all 5 flavors.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
This cake is good for several days.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save broth to boil noodles in.

title: country casserole
directions: Place potatoes and carrots in casserole dish.
Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Pour over potatoes and carrots.
On top of meat, mix and pour 1 can tomato sauce.
Bake for 1 hour. First 30 minutes, bake with lid on and last 30 minutes take lid off.

title: diabetic pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick.
Rinse handful of coconut and add to filling.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350°.
Non-diabetics can use 1 cup sugar and 1 cup coconut.

title: dorothy's jello salad
directions: Set out cream cheese to soften.
Drain pineapple; save juice. Boil 2 cups water and stir in jello.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Dissolve.
Mix pineapple and softened cream cheese; set aside.
Add 1 3/4 cups liquid pineapple juice and cold water.
Mix in pineapple and cream cheese.
Chill.

title: holiday treat holly wreaths
directions: Cream the butter and cheese; add sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and green food coloring; mix well.
Put through cookie press using star plate; form in wreath shape.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with white frosting. Decorate with cinnamon candies.
Makes 2 dozen.
Enjoy!

title: green beans oriental
directions: Drain and mix together beans, sprouts and water chestnuts. Mix together soup and soy sauce.
Add to bean mixture with one cup water and mix well.
Place in large casserole and sprinkle top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cream of tartar 1 minute.
Drop Ritz crackers in boiling syrup and boil 2 minutes.
Add butter and cinnamon.
Bake at 350°.
Use any pie crust.
Makes a two-crust pie.
Tastes like apple pie.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bar english toffee pecan pie
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9-inch uncooked pie shell with broken Heath bars.
Then in a mixing bowl, combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix well and add pecans.
Pour mixture over the Heath bars in the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until wooden pick should come out clean.

title: breakfast egg dish
directions: Place crescent rolls in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix in sausage, hash browns and Cheddar cheese on top of rolls.
Pour eggs, beaten with milk, over other ingredients.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ira salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water and let cool down to room temperature.
Mix in Miracle Whip and mix well.
Add milk and mix, then add pineapple and cottage cheese.
You can add nuts if you wish.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cola roast
directions: Place unseasoned roast
in
baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Pour
in
Coke.
Cover
and seal tightly with aluminum foil.
Roast in oven at 300° until tender.
Time will vary with size of roast.
A 4 pound roast will take 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together. Form into small balls. Fry in the shortening. Drain.
In a saucepan, mix the chili sauce and jelly.
Pour over meatballs and serve warm.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute ground meat, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
Cook instant potatoes separately.
Place cooked ground meat (drained), onion and bell pepper in casserole dish.
Add instant potatoes, then layer meat, then potatoes until it reaches the top.
Add Cheddar cheese on top of potatoes and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: cherry-whip pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla flavoring.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour mixture into crust.
Freeze until firm, 3 hours.

title: orange pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add pumpkin, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Frost while still warm.

title: raspberry chicken salad
directions: Combine nectar, oils, vinegar, basil, mustard, pepper and salt. Put in a jar and shake thoroughly. (May be stored in fridge for 2 wks.)

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cake is done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Can be served plain or with Lemon Glaze.

title: baked pineapple(excellent for diabetics)
directions: Pour pineapple into dish (do not drain).
Add Equal and flour. Beat eggs and add.
Spray 2-quart casserole with Pam and pour in mixture.
Crumble bread over the top.
Cut oleo very thin and lay over top of bread.
Bake 1 hour in oven at 375°.
If getting too brown, reduce heat a little.

title: yummy smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Little Smokies, in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Boil 5 minutes. Reduce heat; add Little Smokies and simmer 5 minutes.
Keep warm over low heat in a chafing dish or slow cooker.

title: jackie's lemon sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375°.
Test with knife after 45 minutes.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix together and roll into a ball.
When cooled in refrigerator, roll in chopped nuts.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients including only 2 cups of cheese.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until set and light brown (about 30 minutes).
Cut into 2 x 1-inch squares.
Yield:
48 squares.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Note:
Line wire rack with foil and several layers of newspaper to prevent spotting.

title: three layer pie
directions: Melt oleo and pour over flour and nuts; mix and press into 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake in a greased loaf pan, 9 x 5-inch, for 70 minutes at 350°.

title: ann's chicken noodle casserole
directions: Prepare Kraft noodles per box directions.
While noodles cook, dice small chunks of chicken breast making 3/4 to 1 cup (or make as meaty as you like).
In medium size saucepan, prepare the chicken sauce as directed (warm water works best).
When it begins to thicken, add diced chicken, drained peas and parsley.
Continue to cook until thick and everything is hot.
Mix with drained noodles.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve hot.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash apples, peel, core and cut into wedges. Dip apple wedges in buttermilk, dredge in flour. Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown. Roll in powdered sugar and cinnamon mix. Serve hot.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Mix ingredients together and add spinach.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Can be frozen for later use.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Put onions, sugar, mustard, garlic and vinegar in frying pan. Cook 20 minutes (simmer) covered.
Add to beans and bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: 8 day pickles sweet
directions: Wash and cut pickles into chunks.
Place in bowl or roaster. (Make use of large pickles.)
Add salt and 1 gallon boiling water. Let stand for 3 days.

title: chicken cacciatore(international:  italy)
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In a large frypan, brown chicken in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except pepper and mushrooms.
Stir well.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with noodles.

title: fruit fantasy
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Save fluid if needed later.
Add cherries, sliced in half.
Add marshmallows and grated coconut. Add sour cream and chopped pecans.
Mix well; chill overnight to ensure flavors are well mixed.

title: mi casa red salsa
directions: In a large, non metal bowl, stir together all ingredients. Cover and place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: scripture cake(king james version)
directions: Stir all the ingredients together until smooth.
Put in a greased and floured Bundt pan or angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Share with lots of people, it's big!

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 13x9 inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup orange juice with remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl. Blend at low speed of mixer for 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes. Drizzle remaining orange juice over warm cake.
Sprinkle with topping made with 1/3 cup sugar, 1/4 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: refrigerated pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onion.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Bring to boil sugar and vinegar; boil 3 minutes.
Let stand.
Add mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over drained cucumbers.	Pack into jars or carton.
Do not seal.
Refrigerate a week or two.
They are ready to use.

title: mexican-style baked chicken
directions: Split, bone and skin breasts, (skin thighs), rinse and pat dry.
Set aside.
In a shallow bowl, beat eggs, garlic and 1/4 cup salsa.
In another shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, chili powder, cumin and oregano.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture to coat; drain briefly, then coat in crumb mixture.
Shake off excess.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix as given; pour into well-greased skillet or pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break the cauliflower into florets and cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and transfer to a bowl.
Cool to lukewarm, then refrigerate for at least one hour.
Put all the remaining ingredients into a bowl.
Add the chilled cauliflower and toss.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: red stew(serves 6)
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Place meat in ovenproof pot.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Cover and bake at 325° for approximately 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Check the pot several times, turning meat over and adding additional liquid if necessary.

title: marvelous marble fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with plastic wrap.
In a 2-quart saucepan, stir corn syrup and milk.
Add chocolate.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium to low heat until chocolate is melted; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add sugar.
With wooden spoon, beat until smooth.
Spread in pan.
Drop peanut butter by teaspoonfuls onto fudge.
With knife, swirl peanut butter through fudge to marbleize.
Chill 2 hours, or until firm.
Invert onto cutting board; peel off plastic wrap.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Yields 25 squares.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine or shortening and sugar until light. Add melted chocolate.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla.
Sift and measure flour with cream of tartar and salt.
Add milk. Measure baking soda in a cup and add boiling water.
Add this quickly to cake mix and stir well.
Pour into a well-greased 12 x 8 x 1 1/2-inches deep or 10-inch square pan, 2-inches deep.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; roll into ball and chill. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: frozen yogurt pops
directions: In
bowl,
sprinkle gelatine over water and let stand 5 minutes.
Place
bowl
inside
second bowl of hot water.
Stir until gelatine dissolves and is clear.

title: short ribs in beer
directions: Flour the beef and brown in half the butter.
Add parsley, pepper, bay leaf, wine vinegar and beer.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until beef is tender.
In remaining butter, saute the sliced onions and add the sugar to glaze them.
When done, add to beef and cook 15 minutes more.

title: swiss steak
directions: Rub salt, allspice and pepper well into steak.
Coat steak with flour.
Heat shortening in pan.
Brown meat quickly in hot pan on both sides.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
You may need to add a little hot water or tomato to prevent sticking.

title: shrimp and oyster gumbo
directions: Make roux from cooking oil and flour, using more or less as needed.
Stir constantly until very brown.
Add onions and garlic and saute until onions are soft, but not browned.
Add tomatoes, fish or chicken broth or stock, and shrimp.
If broth is too thick, add water.
Put in bay leaves and simmer about 30 minutes.
Add seafood seasoning and simmer 45 minutes more.
Add okra, salt and pepper to taste.
Continue to simmer about 5 minutes.
Add oysters and continue to simmer about 10 more minutes or until edges of oysters curl.
Turn off heat and add seafood file powder before serving.
Serve over rice.
This amount makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine in a small skillet.
Add broccoli, cheese, milk and rice.
Bake in a covered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together; bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tested done. Bake in a greased floured pan (oblong, Bundt or 2 layers).
Let cool before frosting.

title: chicken tortilla bake
directions: In a bowl, combine chicken, green chilies, broth, soups and onion; set aside. Warm tortillas according to package directions. Layer half of tortillas on bottom of a greased 9 x 13 casserole dish (cut tortillas to fit dish). Top with half of chicken mixture and half of cheese. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: low sugar dessert
directions: Prepare gelatin by quick-soft method on package and place in refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes, removing when partly set.
Tear cake into chunks.
Place into Bundt pan loosely.
Pour partly set gelatin over cake chunks.
Place in refrigerator until well set. Turn out onto platter.
Ice with Cool Whip and add red cinnamon drops for garnish.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in a quart jar and store in the refrigerator.
It will thicken as it sets.
Makes equivalent of 2 cans.
Use 1 1/4 cups in place of a can of Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.

title: dubin sangria
directions: Mix wine, water and sugar together; mix well until sugar is dissolved.
Add fruit; leave to chill a while in refrigerator.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together in large dish with 1-inch edge.
Pour taco sauce on top.
Chop scallions, tomatoes and olives.
Put on top 1 at a time.
Spread bag of white, then orange cheese on top.
Serve with corn chips.

title: tipsies
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate over hot, not boiling, water.
Add corn syrup and bourbon.
Combine crushed vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and nuts.
Add to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Let crisp in covered container at least several days.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, syrup and butter.
Boil until it makes soft ball.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour out into buttered pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: Press garlic into large microwave-safe bowl. Chop onion and bell pepper; add to garlic. Add pepper and margarine. Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes. Add potatoes, corn and chicken broth to other mixture. Microwave on High 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring once halfway through cooking time. Stir in half and half; microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes more. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add beans, onion and soup.
Heat 10 minutes.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: luau sauce for ribs, chicken or pork
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and process on high until smooth. Pour into clean jars with lids. This will keep in the refrigerator indefinitely.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring 1 1/2 quarts water and instant coffee (dry) to rolling boil and let cool!
Bring 1 1/2 quarts water and 3 pounds sugar to boil and let cool!
Blend the two mixtures together.
Add the alcohol and vanilla.
Blend well.
Let cool.

title: italian goulash
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and bell pepper to well done.
Add chili powder, tomato sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked macaroni and small can corn.
Melt cheese and add to mixture.

title: hershey kiss cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, and peanut butter. Use tablespoon full of dough and roll into ball (flour hands). Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook for 12 to 14 minutes at 350. Press a kiss in the middle of each cookie and let cool.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick.	Cut and fry in deep fat (or oil) to a light brown.
Roll in sugar.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet and saute rice until golden brown. Add vegetables and seasonings and saute 1 to 2 minutes more. Add water or broth and tomato sauce. Bring to boil. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 3 to 4 minutes longer. Fluff and serve. Yum! Freezes very well in bag.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool. Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and drain.
Add bacon which has been cooked crisp and crumbled along with the onion, which has been separated into rings and egg.
Combine oil, vinegar, salt, oregano and pepper in a jar with a lid and shake well.
Pour over spinach mixture and toss.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange marmalade muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups or line with paper bake cups.
Stir together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Make a well in the center.
Combine eggs, sour cream, marmalade, butter and vanilla. Add sour cream mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Fill the muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake them in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Beat in eggs and ReaLemon juice.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with pie filling.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake by directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Take cream cheese and powdered sugar; melt margarine and mix with softened cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on cake and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Put rhubarb into large cake pan. Add pineapple. Sprinkle sugar and corn starch mixture over rhubarb. Dissolve Jell-O and pour over rhubarb. Dot with butter, then cover with pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until crust is brown and rhubarb is soft.

title: microwave sweet potatoes-pineapple(glazed)
directions: Mash potatoes until smooth in
a 1-quart casserole (glass). Drain pineapple, reserving juice (1/4 cup).
Stir 1/4 cup reserved juice and marshmallow cream into potatoes.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until heated in center.

title: tomato soup
directions: Boil tomatoes.
Add butter, salt, pepper and soda.
Thicken with water and cornstarch (mix and add to tomatoes).
Add Milnot and cook over low heat.

title: jalapeno hominy
directions: In medium saucepan, saute margarine, onions, pimiento, mushrooms and jalapenos.
Mix well with hominy and grated cheese. Pour in casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Melt cheese and 1 stick of margarine in a saucepan.
Put broccoli in a casserole dish. Pour cheese and butter mixture over broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers and put on top.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and pour over crackers. Bake in 350° oven for just a few minutes, just to heat before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add the fruits.
Pour in dish and chill until firm.
Prepare cheesecake mix according to package and pour on top of jello mixture.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: 5 hour casserole
directions: Spread in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours and don't peek.

title: sauerkraut a la russe
directions: In hot oil, saute cabbage and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes.
Serves a crowd.

title: potato dish
directions: Dice and boil potatoes. Drain. Add mayonnaise, cheese and onion. Spread in baking dish. Top with bacon and olives. Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat eggs in blender for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat 30 seconds.
Add milk; beat again for 30 seconds.
Then add vanilla and nutmeg; beat for 30 seconds longer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: relish
directions: Soak the first 5 ingredients overnight; drain and soak 3 hours in cold water.
Cook all 20 minutes.

title: special pound cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together on medium speed.
Add icing to batter, 1/3 at a time, beating on low.
Grease and flour Bundt pan and sprinkle nuts on bottom. Pour in batter and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Let cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble. Brown hamburger with chopped onion and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Place peeled eggs in a large heavy jar and cover with liquid.
Let stand for several days before serving for improved flavor.
Can use several pods of sliced garlic, if desired.

title: piccadillo
directions: Brown ground beef in olive oil. Add onions, garlic, sweet pepper and tomatoes. Simmer all. 1/2 hour before serving, add raisins and green olives. Serve over rice.

title: doggie biscuits
directions: Turn oven to 300°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients with a wooden spoon in a large bowl.
Heat chicken broth to lukewarm; add to flour mixture.
Stir until dough forms.
Roll out dough until it is 1/4-inch thick.
Using a large dog biscuit for model, cut out bone shapes from dough.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Brush dough with egg glaze.
Bake bones for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off. Biscuits should remain in oven overnight to harden.
Makes 50 (3 x 1-inch) bones.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend together.
Divide and roll between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Enough for 2 pie crusts.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until tender.
Drain well. Add margarine (reserving 2 tablespoons to dot top).
Mash until smooth.
Add 2/3 of crackers, eggs, milk, sugar, salt and pepper and mix well.
Add cheese.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit and save syrup to mix with sherry.
Layer fruit in a large (4 to 5-quart) casserole, sprinkling with brown sugar, dotting with butter and sprinkling macaroon crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle almonds over all.
Add sherry.
Heat in the microwave for 5 to 6 minutes on High or until bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.
Excellent for parties!

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and baking powder together and then add to the other ingredients.
Mix well and roll out on floured board.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broadway brownie bars
directions: In small mixing bowl, blend 6 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, 1/4 cup butter, 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; set aside.
In medium saucepan over medium heat melt 1 square chocolate and 1/2 cup butter.
Remove from heat; add 1 cup sugar, 1 cup flour, 1 cup nuts, baking powder, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs; blend well.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Spread batter in pan.
Spread cheese mixture over batter. In small bowl, combine 1/4 cup nuts and chocolate chips; sprinkle over cheese layer.
Bake at 350° for about 28 minutes or until almost done.
Sprinkle marshmallows over all; return to oven for 2 minutes.
In medium saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter, 1 square chocolate, 2 ounces cream cheese and milk.
Remove from heat; stir in confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Immediately drizzle over marshmallows.
Chill well; cut into bars.
Yields 30 bars.

title: mushrooms supreme
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove and chop stems.
Saute stems, onion and celery in two tablespoons of butter until soft.
Add parsley.

title: ground beef corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions.
Cook until tender.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into casserole. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley

title: turkey bean casserole
directions: Place turkey in large kettle with water, onion, bay leaf, salt and thyme.
Heat to boiling.
Cover tightly and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Cool.
Debone.
Boil down liquid remaining to 3/4 cup.
Drain some of the liquid from beans.
Add to turkey with tomato paste and sausages and mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Add butter flavor and pecans. Stir until nuts are covered, set aside.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Mix until blended, then add nut mixture.
Put into cupcake cups 3/4 full.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: super duper nachos
directions: Mix together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
In large (really large) dish, spread bean dip and chili.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream-mayo mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Put in a 325° oven for 20 minutes, or zap in microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese on coarse side of grater; let stand at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls. Place on a cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sophia loren's spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add garlic, then blend in other ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Lower heat and cook gently for 30 minutes, stirring every now and then.
Put cooked spaghetti on a large platter; cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with at least 4 tablespoons of grated Parmesan cheese.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and almond paste.
Add eggs, flour, lemon zest, almond and vanilla extract.
Mix well; spread into greased, floured small Bundt pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes, depending on size of pan.

title: giant taco appetizer
directions: Spread bean dip in a circle or shape of platter, leaving room around edge to arrange taco chips.
Spread guacamole over bean dip.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread over guacamole.
Sprinkle tomatoes on top of sour cream layer. Arrange green onions over tomatoes and place black olives over onions.
Top olives with shredded Cheddar.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator no longer than 8 to 10 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: melt in your mouth cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine with powdered sugar and vanilla. Sift flour and cornstarch together; add to margarine mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Beat butter and sugar in medium-size bowl until light colored.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, alternately with bananas and milk.
Stir in 3/4 cup of the nuts.
Pour batter into loaf pan.
Arrange remaining nuts on top. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes.
Run thin knife around edge and remove bread from pan. Cool on rack.
Wrap tightly.
Better the next day.

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix sugar, oil, cake mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add sour cream.
Pour half of batter in pan; sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Pour rest of batter over cinnamon-sugar mixture. Bake at 350°.

title: chicken delmarva
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except chicken.
Set aside. In baking dish, arrange chicken on bottom.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake covered for 1 hour and 1/2 hour uncovered at 350°.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond squares in large microwave-safe bowl.
Stir in peanut butter until creamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients, then drop by spoonful on wax paper or foil; let set.

title: chocolate covered cherry cookies
directions: Mix together the oleo and sugar.
In a separate bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Add first mixture to second mixture.
Roll into balls and press 1 maraschino cherry into each cookie, then put 1 teaspoon of topping on top of cherry.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: stir and drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
With a fork, beat eggs.
Stir in oil, vanilla, lemon and almond extract.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift together baking powder, flour and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Stamp each cookie flat with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
(Lightly oil glass, then dip in sugar.)
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the onions and hamburger.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Blend ingredients with spoon.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes until brown.
Mix and spread the sour cream, cream cheese, dressing and mayo.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Wrap tight with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine olive oil, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, cheese, egg, garlic and pepper in small bowl; mix well.
Combine lettuce and croutons in salad bowl.
Add dressing; toss lightly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 8-inch square cake pan.
Combine ingredients in order listed.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Spoon red sauce over.
Serve.

title: best ever pancakes
directions: In a bowl, sift together the first 4 ingredients three times. In a larger mixing bowl, beat the eggs slightly with a fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add dry ingredients and stir.
Add vanilla and beat mixture by hand to a smooth batter.
Do not use electric mixer.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto hot, ungreased griddle.
Bake until golden brown and bubbles appear over the surface.
Turn. Bake until other side is golden brown.
Serve on heated plates or platter with melted butter or margarine and warm syrup.
This is trouble to make but is well worth it.

title: fire house baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in large heavy pan.
Cook slowly over low heat (stirring often to prevent sticking) about 3 hours or until slightly thickened.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pumpkin pie dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch sprayed dish.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until brown on top. Great with Triscuits.

title: glazed segments
directions: Put segments on cookie sheet, segments should not touch each other.
Place in a low oven for a few minutes to dry.
Be sure segments are dry on both sides.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, and baking powder. Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet, and bake about 12 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Sift 1 1/4 cups sugar, 1 1/4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder together in a separate mixing bowl.
Add 1 1/4 cups milk and stir with spoon until smooth.
Pour over margarine.
Spoon sliced peaches on top of flour mixture with 1/2 of peach juice.
Flour mixture will rise to top to form crust.
Cinnamon may be added to flour mixture at time of sifting if desired.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for approximately 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: cheesy creamy potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes. When tender, drain off water. Add onion dip and margarine to potatoes in large mixing bowl. With electric mixer, beat well. Add half the cheese to potato mixture. Pour into a shallow baking dish and top with rest of shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts (about 15 minutes). This makes a lot and is great for a large gathering.

title: beef and lentil stew
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in mushrooms and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until lentils are tender, about 40 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 (1 1/2 cups each) servings.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and half of flour. Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening.
Gradually beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth; place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally.
About 2 hours before baking, cut off amount needed and return remaining dough to refrigerator.
Shape into rolls and place in greased pan.
Cover. Let rise 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes on stove top in pot.
Then put in buttered casserole.
Mix soup and mayonnaise.
Spread over bread or cracker crumbs, then add cheese.
Then pat more bread or cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cut onion into small pieces which you like.
Cut chicken into small pieces which you like.
Stir 2 eggs in the bowl.
Heat pan (wok) up, then put 2 or 3 spoons of oil.
Cook eggs first and stir them into small pieces.
Put eggs into the bowl, then clean the pan.
Heat the pan up again, then put 3 spoons of oil.
Cook chicken, then onion and rice.
Add some soy sauce and salt.
Put some vegetable that you like.
Enjoy.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all above ingredients in a baking dish and bake for 4 hours uncovered at 300°.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: chex party mix
directions: Heat oven 250.
Melt butter in large roasting pan in oven. Stir in seasonings gradually.
Stir in remaining ingredients until evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 12 cups snack mix.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease. Crumble up and cool. Trim crusts from bread and cut into cubes.
Mix all ingredients together and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan. Refrigerate overnight. When ready to cook, bake 60 minutes at 350°.
Let set for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Add onions, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix and pour in a 1-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crumbs are browned.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain clams.
Add water to measure 1 1/2 cups.
To liquid, add tomatoes, salt, thyme or oregano and pepper.
Add vegetables.
Cook on high until boiling.
Then simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add clams.
Heat through and serve.
It is delicious.

title: new york roast beef
directions: Rub oil over entire surface of meat.
Combine remaining ingredients and rub over roast.
Place in shallow baking dish, fat side up.
Put in preheated 500° oven.
Turn down to 350° and bake 20 minutes per pound.

title: kris kringle cookies
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar a little at a time and cream well.
Add eggs, vanilla, milk to which soda has been added and flour which has been sifted with cream of tartar.
Mix well, adding flour to form a dough that can be rolled.
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter, oil and both sugars.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into sugar mixture.
Blend well.
Roll into small balls and roll them in sugar.
Press down lightly on ungreased cookie sheet with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen large or 12 dozen or more small cookies.
These are very good for special occasions.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Take seeds out of peeled cucumbers and cut in strips.
This will make a dishpan full.
Fill dishpan of pickle strips full of water (cold).
Add lime and let set in lime water for 12 to 17 hours.
Stir occasionally, being careful not to break pickles. Keep covered tightly.
Pour lime water off and wash pickles. Handle carefully.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind cucumbers. Add salt and cover with water. Let stand 3 hours. Grind all vegetables and add to other ingredients. Cook 20 minutes (after hot through). Put in hot sterile jars and let seal.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Alternately layer all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low all day.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add ground pecans and flour. Form into balls size of hickory nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: frozen peach salad
directions: Mix pie filling, peaches, pineapple and Eagle Brand milk.
Add marshmallows and topping.
Pour into large rectangular glass bowl.
Put into freezer until ready to use.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cook corn, butter, salt and water for 15 minutes.
Add meal and stir.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake on 325° for 65 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season
pork chops with garlic powder, pepper and salt. Brown pork
chops
in
hot oil, then layer in 10 1/2 x 14-inch baking pan.
Top pork with potatoes.
Pepper potatoes then top with onion,
mushrooms and soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until
potatoes
are
tender.
About
minutes before removing from
oven,
remove foil and bake, uncovered.
Add a salad and you have a good meal.

title: date cake
directions: Soak chopped dates in boiling water and then mash.
Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Beat in the egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.

title: reese's candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine together.
Add powdered sugar and mix until smooth.
Spread into a cake pan and let cool.
Melt the Hershey bar and spread on top.
Let cool.
Cut into pieces, then refrigerate.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, shortening and bananas together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Just mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken and artichoke casserole
directions: Drain artichokes; dice and arrange in casserole dish.
Dice onion; saute in margarine and pour over artichokes.
Place chicken on top of onion.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cayenne pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Arrange cut up artichoke pieces on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix cooked and drained spinach, mushroom soup, mushrooms and garlic salt.
Spread over artichokes, then spread sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice mixture on top.
Cook for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry angel food de-light
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
When cake has cooled, trim crust and remove from pan.
Cut cake into 3 layers. Prepare whipped topping as directed on package using skim milk. Stir in yogurt, 1/2 the strawberries and the food color.
Spread 1/3 of whipped topping between each layer and on top of cake.
Top with remaining strawberries.
Before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cranberries grand marnier
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and boil 5 minutes more.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar. Fold into mix and chill.
Yields 4 cups.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil and boil for one minute.
Line a prebaked pie shell with strawberries and pour mixture in pie pan over top of strawberries.
Chill thoroughly.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo or butter until onion is wilted. Blend flour in well with this mixture.
Pour in milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt and red and black peppers; cook for 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in a bowl suitable for mixing and pour the cooked sauce over the crabmeat.
Blend well and then transfer to a lightly greased casserole; sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Serves 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix milk, sugar, butter and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake in pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: rice with dal
directions: Note:

If using green Moong dal, because of its hard texture, it will have to be parboiled approximately 20 minutes until semi-soft, drained, and then added to the rice before cooking. Yellow Moong dal is smaller, cooks up very soft, and does not need to be precooked but is added directly with the rice.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in a lightly greased pan. (Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.) Combine wine and soup in saucepan, heating briefly to blend well.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Layer on cheese slices.
Sprinkle with crushed stuffing. Drizzle melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Add soup and corn.
Put in buttered casserole and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ellie's brown sugar coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients in part 1 together and take out 1 cup and set aside to use as a topping.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Combine sugars and spices in 4 quart saucepan.
Add cider; heat, stirring until sugars are dissolved.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Add orange juice and heat.

title: "swedish apple pie"(prep time:  15 minutes; cooking time:  45 minutes)
directions: Place peeled apples into baking dish so that dish is 2/3 full of apples.
Spray a little Pam in dish so pie won't stick. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon over the apples.
Mix melted margarine with 1 cup of sugar.
Add flour and egg.
Mix these ingredients together and pour over the apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Put margarine and cocoa in container.
Microwave 1 minute.
Mix eggs with margarine and cocoa, then add flour and sugar.
Mix with fork together.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Cool 30 minutes.
(Use a greased 9-inch pan with straight edges.)

title: fish pudding
directions: Mix in a 2-quart casserole; cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake until set. Serve with potatoes and slaw.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and cream.
Add vanilla, salt, baking powder, flour and nuts.
Drop by walnut sized balls on cookie sheets.
Dip a glass bottom in sugar and press each ball flat.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: cream of carrot soup(this is a winner!)
directions: In a deep pan, place a dash of Worcestershire and paprika, about 1/2 teaspoon celery salt and 1 tablespoon butter; bring to boiling, then add oysters and clam juice.
Cook until edges of oysters curl.
Add milk; bring to boil and pour into bowl.
Top with 1 tablespoon butter and paprika.

title: don far tong or egg drop soup
directions: Blend the broth, water and tomato paste in a saucepan.
Bring the mixture to a boil over medium heat.
Beat the egg.
Pour the egg slowly into the boiling soup.
The egg should form thin strands.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; put into colander and squeeze to drain.
Mix in stuffing, onions, eggs and oleo.
Mix cheese, Accent and garlic salt, then add to mixture.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Refrigerate over 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain, add taco seasoning and 1 cup of water.
Let simmer.
Add cheese, chopped tomatoes and lettuce. Mix all together.
You can add 1 can of light red kidney beans. Also it can be topped with sliced olives and sour cream.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and add next 5 ingredients.
Combine last 3 ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix, if needed.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheets.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: lawry's fiesta dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve in medium-sized bowls with tortilla chips and fresh cut vegetables such as carrots, broccoli, cauliflower or zucchini sticks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: To each jar add 1/4 teaspoon alum, 1 clove garlic, 1 bay leaf and 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed.
Boil salt, vinegar and water 2 to 3 minutes.
Pack clean pickles in jars.
Pour hot brine over pickles and seal.
Put in boiling water bath and process for 5 minutes. Double recipe is enough for 13 quarts.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
This recipe can be mixed the night before.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together after cheese softens.
Then shape into balls or logs.
Roll in nuts or chopped ham.

title: hot clam dip
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in clam sauce, crumbs and cheese.
Pour into a 2-cup ovenproof dish.
Cover and bake 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crudites or crackers.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread if frozen.
Cut or tear bread/biscuits into walnut sized pieces and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 to 60 minutes before baking.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly and invert onto foil.

title: trailside oatmeal treats
directions: Beat oleo, peanut butter and sugars until creamy.
Stir in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal and nuts, raisins or chocolate chips, if used.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by tablespoon 3-inches apart.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 42 cookies.

title: sour cream chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine well; add eggs.
Add sour cream and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture, then add chips.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: um um corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased skillet and bake at 400° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: ashleys hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In large pan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tortellinis.
Cook 20 minutes longer.

title: banana cake and frosting
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, bananas and eggs (1 at a time) together.
Mix well.
Add soda, salt, nutmeg and flour.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° or in layer pans at 375°.

title: wild rice oven pilaf
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine boiling water and butter; stir until butter is melted.
Stir in brown rice, wild rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bake in a 375° oven for 70 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in carrots and frozen peas.
Cover and bake about 10 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Makes 4 to 6 side dish servings.

title: cheese and crab appetizer
directions: Mix well the cream cheese and salad dressing and form into a long roll.
Flatten to about 1 inch.
Cover with cocktail sauce. Drain the crabmeat well and spread on top.
Serve with crackers. This looks good on a green base like lettuce.

title: yummy cinnamon rolls
directions: Thaw frozen bread but don't let raise.
Break 1 loaf of bread into pieces and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon over dough.
(Sprinkle nuts.)

title: crisp cookies
directions: To make a soft dough, combine butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs, baking soda, cream of tartar and 1 pint of flour to start.
Roll out and cut.
Spread a little milk on top and sprinkle remainder of sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon on top.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until light brown.

title: fudge cake
directions: Combine water, shortening and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to boil; pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in sheet pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbling; put chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer a package of frozen broccoli on top of chicken.
Put sauce over.
Cook until broccoli is tender at 350°, about 1 hour.

title: quick boiled frosting
directions: Bring butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight. Drain before serving.
Serves 12 and keeps several days.

title: chocolate nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and chop coarsely.
Mix artichokes with remaining ingredients.
Place in greased 1/2-quart baking-serving dish.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin custard cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin.
Melt butter. Pour over dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fried apples
directions: Slice apples in 1/8-inch slices.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Coat apples.
Melt butter in nonstick skillet.
Saute 7 to 8 minutes.
Serve at once.
Good with ham or pork.

title: crab meat on english muffin
directions: Melt all in double boiler.
Spread on English muffins and place in toaster oven until brown.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Start cake in a cold oven, turn to 300° and bake an hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and place in greased casserole dish.
Add can of mushroom pieces or water chestnuts (optional).
Place salted and peppered cut chicken pieces on top and bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes (depends on size of chicken pieces; breasts take longer to cook).
I have used seasoned salt to give extra flavor to chicken or you can use any spices you like.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Pat biscuits into 3 1/2-inch circle. Fit dough over back of well-greased muffin tins. Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
Makes 10.

title: kids carrots
directions: If your kids don't eat carrots, try this.
No need to worry about the alcohol in the vermouth.
It completely cooks out leaving the sweet flavor!

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: You will need miniature muffin pan.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: In bowl beat eggs with oil; stir in sugar, zucchini, carrots and vanilla.
Mix together flour, All-Bran, salt, soda and cinnamon; stir into zucchini mixture.
Add nuts and mix well. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Allow to cool 15 minutes, then cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked squash, except stuffing.
Butter a casserole dish and place a layer of stuffing on the bottom.
Top with squash mixture.
Repeat, ending with stuffing on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, just to brown.

title: chicken in sauce over brown rice
directions: Saut green onion, garlic and green pepper in olive oil. Add flour, several tablespoons; stir until a paste forms. Add chicken stock in proportion of about 1 cup of broth to 2 tablespoons of flour to make the amount you want. Add chunks of carrots, seasonings and about 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese. Add wine, if using. (It does perk it up a bit.)
Cook until

carrots are just done. Add diced, cooked chicken. Serve over seasoned brown rice. You can adjust the recipe according to the amount of chicken you have or how much of it you want in the sauce. Serves about 6; depends on amount you use. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: cry baby cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, milk, molasses and soda. Add dry ingredients sifted together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Grease and flour 4 one pound cans, fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool completely in can.
May be frozen.

title: creamy mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and stir until thoroughly combined. Slowly add chicken broth, stirring until smooth. Stir in half and half and parsley. Season with salt and pepper.
Heat just until mixture simmers. Serve over chicken breasts or toast points.

title: saucy franks
directions: Cook onion in hot fat over medium heat until tender, but not brown. Stir in catsup, water, vinegar, sugar, relish, salt and pepper.
Add frankfurters to sauce in skillet.
Lower temperature to simmer.
Cover and simmer until frankfurters are cooked.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
It makes a little more than a quart.
It keeps well in the refrigerator or unrefrigerated.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream oleo or butter; add sugar.
Blend melted chocolate; add vanilla and 1 egg and beat 5 minutes exactly; add 1 more egg and beat 5 minutes more.
Turn into baked shell.
Add whipped cream and slivered walnuts.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Hull and wash strawberries, fill pie shell with strawberries. In a medium saucepan over low heat, cook sugar, water and cornstarch until it boils, stirring constantly.
Continue to boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add strawberry gelatin.
While still hot, pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Refrigerate top with whipped cream when cool.

title: white chili (chicken chili)
directions: Rinse beans and place in Dutch oven; add water.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat.
Simmer for several minutes.
Remove from heat and let beans soak for 1 hour (or overnight).
Drain off water.

title: honey baked chicken
