directions: Shake together in bag to coat the chicken breast halves, flour and pepper.
In a small saucepan melt butter.
Pour half of it in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken in pan.
Turn to coat. Bake skin side down for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef-cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Transfer to large pot. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Serve with corn bread.

title: whole grain jam squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves in large mixing bowl. Beat at low speed on mixer until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups mixture.
Press remaining onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread preserves evenly over base; sprinkle with reserved mixture.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: oreo supreme
directions: Crush cookies finely; set aside. In bowl, mix sour cream and milk with whisk until well blended. Stir in instant pudding, mixing well. Stir in crushed cookies, but save some to sprinkle on top. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into bowl and sprinkle cookie crumbs on top. Eat now or can be refrigerated for later.

title: potato bake
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Combine and mix all ingredients.
Turn into greased casserole.
Bake, covered, for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
(Serves 8.)

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Put cake mix in a bowl; remove 2/3 cup and save for later. Add 1 egg and margarine.
Mix and pat into a greased 9x13 pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Stir pretzels together with sugar and margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press to bottom.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In order listed, layer ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Mix meat with wild rice and soups.
Add water, mushrooms, almonds and soy sauce in crock-pot. Cook on low 12 hours.

title: easy crust apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine apples, cinnamon and nutmeg; stir to coat apples with spices.
Place apples in a greased 9-inch pan.
In medium bowl, combine sugar, 1/2 cup of the baking mix, milk, eggs and 2 tablespoons butter; beat until smooth and spoon mixture over apples, then set aside.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1 cup baking mix, pecans, brown sugar and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until apples are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pudding pie
directions: In a saucepan, whisk the milk and pudding mix. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.

title: cheese ball
directions: Save 3/4 of 1 package dried beef to roll ball in.
Chop beef and onions extremely fine.
Mix well.
Form into ball and roll in balance of chopped beef.
Chill.

title: too easy tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring broth to a boil. Stir in tortellini. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans, tomatoes and basil. Simmer for 4 to 6 minutes or until pasta is tender. Stir in vinegar and pepper. Serves 6.

title: sherry bisque
directions: Combine 4 cups beef stock, split peas, ham hock and bay leaf in a heavy medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce and let simmer until ready to use.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter until soft.
Cook rice in 1 cup boiling water. Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: cocoa fudge frosting
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add cocoa; heat 1 minute or until smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into mixer bowl. Alternately add sugar and milk.
Beat to a spreading consistency. Blend in vanilla.

title: stobys cheese dip
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil in large Dutch oven.
Add Velveeta.
Mix butter and flour to a paste.
Add to cheese mixture.
Stir until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Spread half of the sweet potatoes in the bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Top with half of apples and marshmallows.
Repeat layers with remaining potatoes, apples and marshmallows.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon; sprinkle over casserole.
Dissolve cornstarch in water; pour over sugar mixture.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white chili(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Bake the chicken breasts at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let them cool and cut or tear into bite size pieces.
Add chicken to chicken stock mixture.
Combine chicken broth, white Northern beans, white kidney beans, cumin, oregano, chili powder, red pepper and hot sauces in a 6-quart stockpot.
Saut garlic and onions in olive oil until tender.
Add green chilies and saut 2 more minutes.
Add to other ingredients.
Cook for an hour and serve.

title: ma's soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Chill at least 4 hours and roll to desired thickness.
Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Flour and brown beef in a skillet.
Season with garlic salt and cloves while browning.
Fill stew pot 1/2 full with water and 1 tsp. beef bouillon.
Dice onions and combine with beef.
Add beef and onions to water and let simmer for 2 - 3 hours.
Cut potatoes and carrots in bite size pieces and add to beef.
Add butter and simmer until vegetables are fully cooked.

title: passover nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and egg yolks until light yellow.
Add juice, rind, oil and water; mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
With clean and dry blades, beat egg whites until they are stiff (just until they leave peaks when blades are lifted).
Do not overbeat.
Fold into other ingredients very well. Do not beat.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Roll in marble size balls and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: zap it!  rice
directions: Combine water and butter in a 2-cup glass measure.
Cover and microwave on High 2 minutes until boiling.
Add rice.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: deborah nelson's batter for deep frying vegetables
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and egg until smooth.
Prepare vegetables to bite size pieces.
Heat oil to 375° and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, margarine and light brown sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Sift and measure flour, baking powder and salt.
To the creamed mixture, add the flour mixture and undiluted evaporated milk.
Add flavoring or vanilla and mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb pecan muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and nuts.
In another bowl, combine egg, oil, orange peel and orange juice; add to dry ingredients all at once and stir just until moistened.
Stir in rhubarb.
Fill 12 lightly greased muffin cups almost to top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yield:
about 1 dozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix vegetables and dressing together.
Add spaghetti and Salad Supreme spice.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: m&m chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix until smooth butter, white sugar and dark brown sugar. Add vanilla, egg, flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix should be firm, not too moist.
Add 1 cup smashed M&M's; fold in.
Then add whole M&M's (rest of a 3/4 pound bag).
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Can do ahead.
Can freeze.

title: "gold" nugget chicken(appetizer)
directions: Toss chicken and oil. Mix remaining ingredients except Apricot Honey Sauce in plastic bag.
Shake about 6 pieces chicken at a time in bag until coated. Shake off excess crumbs.

Arrange chicken pieces in single layer in pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes, rotating pie plate 1/2 turn after 3 minutes, or until juices run clear.
Serve with Apricot Honey Sauce.

title: persimmon pudding(makes 12 servings)
directions: Combine persimmon, sugar, eggs, flour, soda, baking powder, spices and salt.
Blend with mixer.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture in 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until set and brown.
Serve when cool with whipped cream if desired.

title: grape and blueberry salad
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and congeal.
Beat the Dream Whip, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Add the cream cheese and spread on top of the congealed salad.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in three pans at 325° or 350° until done.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: porkie pines
directions: Pressure cook 15 to 20 minutes; then pour 1 small can tomato sauce over after cooked.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
and
bake
at 350° for 1 hour. Put in tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday fruit bars
directions: Combine all ingredients to make stiff paste.
Pack tightly in pan lined with foil.
Bake at 375° until done.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: nectarine cobbler(peach)
directions: Peel and slice fruit into large bowl, add 1 cup sugar and lemon juice and toss.
Let stand 4 hours or overnight to exude juices.

title: herb seasoning salt
directions: Mix together in a jar onion powder, garlic powder and pepper. Add thyme and salt, then add marjoram, oregano, rosemary, basil and parsley.
Last, but not least, add sesame seed.
Secure lid and shake well.
Makes one cup.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Cook together the sugars, milk, salt and cream of tartar, stirring constantly, until forms soft ball or until thermometer registers 240°.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir until margarine melts.
Beat a minute or two.
Add pecans; continue to beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop quickly onto waxed paper by small spoonfuls.
Let cool until firm.
Makes about 50 (2-inch) pralines.

title: butterscotch thins
directions: Melt morsels with butter over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together. Stir into butterscotch mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill.

title: fried cabbage supreme
directions: Fry bacon or sausage in large pan.
Add onion, garlic, potatoes and cabbage.
Simmer mixture until it turns light brown. Stir frequently.
Pour in chicken broth; add salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Cover; simmer until brown.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Beat egg white with 1 teaspoon each salt and water.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cover, let rise in a warm place until doubled, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Punch down dough; divide into 12 equal balls.
Roll each out with palms of hands on floured surface to form 18 inch long ropes.
Twist into pretzel shape, tucking ends under.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Let rise, uncovered (until puffy), 20 to 25 minutes.
Brush lightly with egg white mixture.
Sprinkle with caraway seed or coarse salt.
Bake at 425° until well browned, 12 to 15 minutes.
Good served warm with cheese sauce.

title: light and zesty chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar together.
Add milk and stir well. Place over fire.
Bring to boiling point and boil gently until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Do not stir during
the boiling process.
Remove from fire.
Add butter or oleo
and let cool.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into
buttered pan and mark into squares before it hardens.

title: summer potato salad
directions: Pare potatoes.
Cover with water.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Cool and chill.
Blend together mayonnaise, sour cream, celery and onion.
Add bacon.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Gently fold in potatoes.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: carrot pie
directions: Beat eggs and milk slightly.
Add well blended dry ingredients.
Add carrots and mix well.
Pour into pie pan lined with unbaked pastry.
Bake in hot 450° oven for 10 minutes or until set. Cool and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: waldorf astoria stew
directions: Mix all together and bake in a large covered casserole for 5 hours at 250°.
Do not peek or raise cover during baking.
Bake for a full 5 hours.

title: smothered steak
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Brown meat in Crisco.
Take meat out. Saute the onions into the rest of Crisco.
Add 4 Tbsp. flour, mixing well.
Add water in which bouillon cubes or granules have been dissolved.
Place meat in baking dish and pour bouillon mixture on top.
Cover and bake at 325°F for 2 hrs.
This makes its own gravy and is great served with mashed potatoes.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: broccoli casserole #2
directions: Cook
broccoli	5
to
10 minutes; drain well.	Mix all ingredients
except
crumbs.
Pour	into
buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole
dish.
Sprinkle	cracker crumbs on top and dot with margarine.	Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread about a teaspoon of cream cheese on each ham slice. Roll lengthwise.
Place the olive on top of the roll with a toothpick.
Chill before serving with fresh vegetables.

title: salad cacciatori
directions: Mix chicken, celery and shells together.
Make dressing with remaining ingredients.
Mix dressing with chicken mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand for 3 hours before serving.

title: jelly roll dessert
directions: Cut jelly roll in thin slices.
Line punch bowl.
Be sure you can see red layer on sides of bowl.
Cover thinly with strawberry topping.
Layer with pudding, then Cool Whip, few cherries and nuts until bowl is full.
Makes a large bowl.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 1-quart greased casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate blueble bars
directions: In large bowl stir together flour, sugar, nuts, butter and egg until crumbly.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups of this mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Spread jam over the top.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Crumble remaining mixture over the top.
Bake 40-45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: braised short ribs
directions: In a 12-inch Dutch oven, brown ribs (fat side down) for 30 minutes.
Discard
drippings.
Add	onions,
garlic,
beef broth, steak sauce, marjoram, peppercorns, bay leaf and 1 cup water. Bring to a boil and then simmer, covered, for 2 hours. Remove meat and skim fat from Dutch oven.
Mix flour with 1/2 cup water. Stir
into Dutch oven and boil for 3 minutes. Pour over ribs.

title: hungarian pie(dessert)
directions: Cream the egg and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake in greased pie pan at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: snickers bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening over hot (not boiling) water and pour half into an 8-inch square pan that has been lined with foil. Refrigerate until firm.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Boil and dry hot dogs before dipping in mixture.
Fry in hot oil on medium-high until browned.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and use as part of the 2 cups of cold water to prepare the jello.
After jello slightly sets, add the rest of the ingredients.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper.
Save broth.
Pull bone off chicken.
Boil vermicelli in chicken broth.
Cook broccoli as directed on package (but add no salt).
Drain broccoli.

title: reuben casserole(microwave)
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Spread mustard evenly on bread.
Cut bread in small squares.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Crumble corned beef over bread.
In mixing bowl, mix sauerkraut, soup, water and relish until well blended. Spoon over corned beef; cover dish loosely with waxed paper and microwave 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove waxed paper and place cheese on top to cover.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Let stand uncovered for 5 minutes, then serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, milk and vanilla. Add eggs. Beat well. Add coconut. Pour in deep pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana pecan torte
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Beat in bananas and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to cool completely.

title: sweet and sour stew
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add salt, tomatoes, sugar, vinegar, onion and bay leaf.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add pepper last 10 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: mom's famous banana bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl. Add bananas and eggs to mix. Combine flour, salt and baking soda to ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes. Makes 2-2 1/2 loaves of bread.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Blend eggs and sugar. Add other ingredients; stir well. Spread on well-greased and floured cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool on waxed paper. Place another sheet of waxed paper on top; roll up and cool for 45 minutes. Make filling while cooling.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in small amount of boiling salted water until crisp done (about 8 minutes).
Drain and mix with next 3 ingredients in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss the bread crumbs, almonds and butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: spicy barbecue balls
directions: Mix sausage, bread crumbs and eggs with hands and roll into balls.
Fry in skillet until golden brown.
Drain and put in crock-pot.
In bowl, mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Simmer in crock-pot for 1 hour.

title: new york cheesecake
directions: Blend cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar, and 1/4 cup melted butter and line the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch ungreased spring-form pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place deboned chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Drain mixed vegetables and place on top of chicken.
In a medium bowl, mix soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
In another bowl, mix Bisquick, butter and milk and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream over low heat. Melt butter in frypan, add stuffing mix to butter.
Lay broccoli, then soup mixture, then stuffing mix in a rectangle baking pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until stuffing is browned.

title: chicken cassia tore
directions: Cook and stir chicken, onion, and pepper strips in oil until lightly browned. Add all other ingredients except rice. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese and pecan danish
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unfold pastry; roll to 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Place in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, egg and vanilla in small mixing bowl at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread cream cheese mixture over pastry to within 3 inches from outer edges.
Make 2-inch cuts at 1-inch intervals on long sides of pastry.
Crisscross strips over filling.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Drizzle with glaze.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix all vegetables with 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain.
Put spices into a bag.
Add to vegetables all other ingredients.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles until almost done.
Brown ground beef; drain and add other ingredients, except cheeses.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill greased pan by alternating noodles, Mozzarella cheese, sauce/beef mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: "no time for dessert" dessert
directions: Break cake into bite-size pieces; stir in pie filling.
Reserve enough Cool Whip (about 1/2) to spread on top.
Then add rest of Cool Whip to cake and pie filling.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan; top with reserved Cool Whip and chopped nuts, then chill.
Gets better by second day.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, paprika, dry mustard, salt, pepper, and garlic powder in a plastic bag. Shake chicken pieces in flour mixture, one piece at a time. Lay in a single layer on baking pan that has been greased with margarine. Dot with more margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, turning over once. Turn oven up to 450° and bake 10-15 minutes longer until chicken is brown and bubbling.

title: homemade pastry
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour and salt.
Using a pastry blender or two forks, cut in the shortening until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the water over part of the mixture, then gently toss with a fork.
Push the moistened mixture to the side of the bowl.
Repeat using 1 tablespoon of the water at a time, until all the dough is moistened.
Form dough in a ball.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine in one bowl the grated raw apples with egg. Mix well. Add sugar and cooking oil.
Stir.
Add nuts, vanilla and cinnamon, stirring well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to first mixture and blend well.
Turn into greased oblong pan.
Bake in a preheated oven for about 40 minutes or
until done.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Sift dry ingredients and 2 tablespoons of the sugar altogether.
Work in butter with processor until like corn meal. Put in an 8-inch square, ungreased pan and pat the above mixture up on sides and bottom of pan.
Put peach halves over pastry. Sprinkle cinnamon and remaining sugar over peach halves.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mix 2 eggs and cream together and pour over peaches and pastry.
Bake for 20 or 30 minutes longer.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni per directions.
Cool with cold water; drain. Put in a bowl.
Slice cucumber and carrots into bowl.
Put Miracle Whip in.
Mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: lady bird johnson's spinach parmesan
directions: Place cooked, cleaned spinach
in
water
(or may steam same). Drain thoroughly and chop coarsely.
Add cheese, onion, cream and 4 tablespoons
butter.
Arrange
in
shallow
baking dish and sprinkle with
crumbs
mixed
with	remaining butter. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine potato, vanilla and butter.
Work in powdered sugar until stiff, then roll out like pie dough.
Cover with creamy peanut butter and roll up jelly roll style.
Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add butter (melted) and mix well.
Press into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix butter, brown sugar and corn syrup; blend well.
Pour into a round cake pan. Sprinkle pecans in pan on top of other ingredients.
Dip each breadstick coil in cinnamon and sugar.
Lay buns on top of syrup-pecan mixture.
Bake for 19 to 24 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and invert onto serving pan.

title: roman broccoli
directions: Saute broccoli in oil for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt. Cover with wine and simmer until tender.
Drain.
Sprinkle with butter and cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cucumber pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta.
Toss with olive oil so pasta doesn't stick together.
Mix with cucumber, onion and pimento.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Fold together gently. Refrigerate.
Serve in a pretty crystal bowl.
(Bananas can be added if you like.)

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch tube pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Butter again.
In a large size bowl, combine eggs, sweetened condensed milk, mincemeat, fruits and nuts; mix well.
Add corn flake crumbs (only corn flake crumbs will do) and baking soda; blend well. Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in a slow (300°) oven 2 hours (or until a cake tester comes out clean).
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Turn out of pan; remove paper.
Cool.
If desired, decorate with glazed cherries.
To store, wrap well in aluminum foil and refrigerate or freeze.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for about 5 minutes, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: sarah's spoon bread
directions: Heat milk over medium heat until film forms.
Melt shortening in milk.
Let cool to room temperature.
Sprinkle yeast over water in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and milk mixture.
Mix well.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Beat in remainder of flour.
Mix well. Cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
With a wooden spoon, beat hard 25 strokes.
Put in pan.
Cover with a towel. Let rise to top of pan (30 minutes).
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes until it sounds hollow.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Trim tops off 4 large tomatoes.
Slice into halves.
Mound your favorite dressing on each half.
Arrange on an oiled baking dish.
Top with Parmesan, Cheddar or Swiss cheese slices.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: delicious snack
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pour over the crackers.
Mix well and let set for at least 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash and drain potatoes.
Add 3/4 stick butter or oleo, eggs, cinnamon, milk, sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Put in baking dish and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add topping.

title: creamy angel hair pasta with lemon
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add oil and saute garlic for 1 minute, or until just golden; do not brown.
Add chicken broth and lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook until pink, about 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to low, add Parmesan cheese, cream and lemon peel; cook about 3 minutes to thoroughly heat, but do not boil.
Season with salt.
Combine shrimp mixture and chopped cilantro with the angel hair pasta; toss to mix.
Serve immediately.

title: rice jardin
directions: Saute onions and zucchini in butter or margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Suitable for freezing.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and salt; add the liquid and knead until firm. Place in plastic bag.
This is an inexpensive product and keeps little hands busy!

title: alabama lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, beat sugar, shortening and 1/2 cup margarine together until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and alternately stir in with buttermilk.
Stir in 1 tablespoon of lemon rind and the lemon juice.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick (when stuck in center of cake) comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: california casserole
directions: Cut steak into cubes and coat with flour and paprika. Brown meat in oil and transfer to 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan. Add onions.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind all together with the rind.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, salt, butter, cream cheese, almond extract, vanilla and egg yolk; blend well.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough, a third at a time to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes with lightly floured cookie cutters.
Place cookies 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Brush with slightly beaten reserved egg white and sprinkle with colored sugar, if desired.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Frost and decorate, if desired.
Yield:
5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cook onion, garlic and oregano in oleo until tender; stir in soup.
Cut zucchini lengthwise, scoop out pulp and seed, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Chop pulp and seeds.
Brown meat, add 1/4 cup sauce, pulp, bread crumbs and salt.
Spoon into shell and put in baking dish.
Pour on remaining sauce.
Cover, bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Top with cheese.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, water and vanilla. Mix well and pour in loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Stir in chili seasoning, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Spread batter over chili.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes or until center is firm.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes, or until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in frying pan, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper.
Combine meat, cooked macaroni and tomatoes (broken in pieces) and turn into a 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cool until thick. Add sliced berries.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Whip together.
Spread over crust and pecans.
Add berry mix.
Cool for 2 hours.

title: cherry-apple jam
directions: Finely chop frozen cherries, reserving juices (3 cups chopped fruit).
In an 8 to 10-quart kettle or Dutch oven, combine cherries, reserved juice, apple and lemon juice.
Add pectin; mix well.
Bring mixture to a boil (full rolling boil); stir in sugar. Bring again to a full boil, stirring often.
Boil hard, uncovered, 1 minute.
Remove from heat; quickly skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Makes 5 pints.

title: crisp pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water 8 hours or overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water several times.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to first mixture and form into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar; place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: five-cup salad
directions: Drain liquid off and mix together.
Maraschino cherries can be added.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix well.
Pour in well buttered and floured pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened (about 10 minutes). Add coconut and pecans. Beat until thick enough to spread. Great for German Chocolate Cake.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into small strips and brown in butter.
Add broth, garlic and paprika.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add sliced onions and peppers.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Start cooking rice. Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Add to meat and vegetables and cook about 2 more minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 3 to 5 minutes more.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Bake one crust.
In skillet melt butter and saute onions and bell pepper.
Add crawfish and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add one can cream of mushroom soup and one tablespoon flour.
Pour into baked crust.
Add raw pie crust on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix chopped onions, corned beef and everything else and form into a ball.
Refrigerate overnight or longer if necessary.
After ball is formed, you can garnish by rolling in finely chopped pecans.

title: orange squares
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add brown sugar and beat well.
Blend in flour, nuts, orange slices (which have been cut up) and vanilla. Turn into buttered baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.
Lift out on waxed paper.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook and stir rice and onion in oil in a 10-inch skillet until rice is golden brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook with onions in water until soft. Drain.
Add crumbs, butter, almost all of the cheese and eggs. Season with salt and pepper.
Add cream and mix in with squash mixture.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 450° until done, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot crossed tuna casserole
directions: Combine everything; spoon into a 10 x 6-inch dish.
Cut dough into 4 long and 8 long strips.
Place strips over casserole in a lattice design.
Brush lightly with mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with additional buttered crumbs and bake 20 minutes longer or until center is firm.

title: apricot-prune coffeecake
directions: In small bowl combine brown sugar, butter, flour and cinnamon; mix with fork until crumbly.
Makes one cup streusel.
Set aside.

title: cherry delights
directions: Mix 1 cup of butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in 1/2 cup light corn syrup, 2 egg yolks and 2 1/2 cups of flour.
Chill.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites and then roll in nuts.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press candied cherry halves into centers.
Bake in 325° oven 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, condensed milk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Then add sweet potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: taco chicken salad(ultra low-fat)
directions: Add chicken pieces to skillet sprayed with cooking spray. Sprinkle with taco seasoning and stir over medium heat.
Add taco sauce and onion flakes and stir.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until all liquid is cooked into meat.
Remove from heat and chill slightly.
Combine this with remaining ingredients.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Chill for a few hours before serving.
Can serve on tortillas or on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with tomatoes and fat-free cheese.

title: breaded pork chops(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, saute garlic in butter on High for 2 minutes.
Combine parsley, salt, cayenne pepper, onion powder, black pepper and bread crumbs together in a flat dish.
Dip chops into garlic butter, then roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle remaining bread crumbs over chops.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High 15 minutes.
Turn chops over and microwave 15 minutes or until well done.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Blend pretzels, butter and sugar together.
Press into 13 x 8 pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whipped topping. Spread over cooled crust and chill.
Make sure this layer is sealed up to sides of dish to keep gelatin from going down into the pretzel layer.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Chill.
Spread over cheese mixture. Chill.

title: pasta and shrimp-cajun style
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Add shallots and garlic; reduce heat to medium-low.
Saute until soft and transparent.
Add tomatoes; cook 5 minutes more.
Stir in tomato paste, Cajun spices and wine and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer.
Add shrimp and simmer 5 more minutes.
Toss cooked pasta with sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients adding pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.

title: vegetable dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until ready to use.
I use sliced carrots, celery, sweet potatoes, broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, radishes, turnips or any other desired vegetable.

title: grape gelatin salad
directions: Mix and chill until set.

title: grilled lamb chops
directions: Brush lamb chop with olive oil, then roll in garlic and rosemary.
Put on grill until done.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Mix well together.
Cover and chill several hours. Serve with crackers.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.
Can be made into a ball and rolled in additional pecans.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, beat eggs and sugar. Add pineapple and mix well.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish. In a medium skillet, melt oleo.
Add bread and cook until cubes are browned, stirring occasionally.
Place bread evenly over pineapple mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: town club dressing
directions: Chop fine anchovies, eggs, parsley and garlic.
Blend all ingredients and chill.
Makes over 1 quart.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook all together until tender, about 1 hour.
Dissolve 1/4 cup flour in 1/2
cup
water;
add	to
sauce
to thicken. Stir. Cook 10 more minutes.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda into bowl.
Add shortening and cut in with pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead 1/2 minute.
Roll 3/8-inch thick; brush with melted butter or margarine.
Fold over, press lightly and cut.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate 12 hours on each side. Makes any inexpensive cut of roast or steak tender and flavorful.

title: homemade eagle brand
directions: Cook over medium-high heat.
Stir constantly until thick.

title: linguini and clam soup
directions: Combine water and salt in soup pot.
Bring to a boil and add linguini.
Bring to boil again and cook until linguini is tender. Stir in the butter and clams. Gradually add the half and half. Heat thoroughly and then stir in the white pepper and cheese.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or at least 1 day.
Serves 8.

title: deep chocolate nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until cookies test done with toothpick.
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Boil chicken and cut into pieces.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put in a casserole dish.
Layer top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix all together well and chill.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs.
Blend well, then stir in the chopped apples.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir in.
Add nuts.
Bake in oblong loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes large, moist cake.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: In medium bowl, mix first 7 ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 45-50 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's oatmeal bread
directions: Add 1/2 cup of warm water to 2 packages dry yeast.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Set aside.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little boiling salt water until tender. Drain.
In saucepan, cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons butter or margarine until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt the remaining butter or margarine. Add remaining cubes and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix spaghetti, eggs and parmesan cheese. Form into spaghetti crust in greased 9 X 13 pan. Top crust with cottage cheese. Heat meat and spaghetti sauce. Pour over cheese and crust. Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Top with shredded mozzarella cheese. Melt, if desired.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, butter, buttermilk and vanilla, then add coconut to fill shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until serving. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: In bowl, mix peaches, sugar, tapioca, flour and nutmeg.
Set aside 5 minutes.
Prepare pie crust. Add fruit to 9-inch pie plate.
Drizzle with lemon juice. Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Slit top for steam to release.
Flute edges and cover edge with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 30 to 35 minutes more, until golden.
Cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Heat the two soups with about a can of water with butter. Drain asparagus and put half in casserole.
Put half soup mixture over this and add cracker crumbs to cover, then 2 sliced eggs. Put slices of cheese over this.
Repeat asparagus, soup, crumbs, eggs and cheese.
Add Pet milk, if not moist enough.

title: luscious lemon poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean 9-inch round cake pans.
Pierce cake with large fork at 1/2-inch intervals.

title: miss baldwin's raisin sauce for ham
directions: Cook water and sugar over low heat for five minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until jelly dissolves.
Makes about 2 cups.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: strawberry soda cake
directions: Make Jell-O as directed and set while baking cake.
Bake cake as directed using 9 x 13-inch pan.
Punch lots of holes in cake. Pour soda over cake.
Pour Jell-O over cake.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Pour over cake.
Refrigerate about an hour before serving.
Spread Cool Whip over cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chili beans
directions: In skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 4 servings.
A family favorite.

title: country chicken soup
directions: Place chicken and water in large pot.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add celery, carrot, onion, bay leaf, potato, salt and pepper to soup.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake 80 minutes at 325°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, bring cocoa, oleo and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan or cookie sheet at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.

title: provence vinaigrette
directions: Stir together the first 6 ingredients.
Gradually whisk in the oil until the mixture is emulsified.
Will keep in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 weeks.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Combine soda, flour and spice. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk (add nuts or raisins).

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Cut in Crisco. Dissolve yeast in warm water for 5 minutes. Add yeast and buttermilk. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn out on floured surface and knead lightly about 10 times. Roll to 1/2 inch thick and cut with a 2 inch cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet, cover and let rise about 45 minutes. Bake in preheated 425° oven about 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: burger-rice bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish (10 x 6 x 2-inch), combine ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until rice is done; stir.
Garnish with sliced, hard-cooked egg, if desired.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Beat raw eggs; add water, vinegar and cook until well blended. Remove from heat and add mustard and Miracle Whip.
Store for weeks in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: easy sour cream and shells
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Mix with sauce and simmer. Cook pasta until tender, but do not overcook.
Layer in casserole dish the sauce, pasta, sour cream and cheese. Continue layering, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Mix all together and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with Doritos or tostadas.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions in large container.
Cover with cracked ice.
Let stand for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain and drop in simmering solution of the remaining ingredients.
Let cucumbers simmer in solution, but do not boil.
Pack in canning jars and seal.

title: chalope
directions: Use large pot or boiler, place Boston butt, pintos, salt, caraway seed, chili powder and jalapeno peppers, covered with water and cook on low to medium heat for 3 to 4 hours or until meat shreds in mixture.
Break up lettuce.
Dip cooked mixture on plate; add 1 serving lettuce, tomatoes, onions, cheese and taco sauce on top; serve with chips.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring chicken, broth and water to boil in a 4 to 5-quart pot. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add carrots, celery and onion.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer until chicken is no longer pink near the bone.
Remove chicken and skim off fat.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix well in casserole dish covered with crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salisbury steak dinners
directions: Grate carrots, celery, green peppers and onions with the food processor.
Grate dried bread with the food processor.
Mix all ingredients together and make into steak patties the size of your hand.
Bake on cookie sheet in oven until done.
You can freeze them by putting wax paper in between each one.
Put gravy over them in a casserole dish when serving and bake in oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; tear apart and mix soup and sour cream.
Crumble crackers and mix with butter.
Sprinkle on top and cook 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mandarin orange cake double batch
directions: Beat together the sugar, eggs and orange slices.
Mix in the flour and baking soda.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cream cheese coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and cream cheese. Gradually add sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Combine flour, soda and salt to creamed mixture. Stir in flavoring. Pour batter into floured and greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until cake test is done. Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb-custard pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour and eggs together.
Add rhubarb.
Place in unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat eggs and 1/4 tsp. salt.
Add flour until you get a soft dough.
Roll half of the dough out as thin as you can on a floured surface.
Cut into four pieces.
Put flour between all four pieces as you stack the four sections on top of one another.
Take your knife and slice thin.
Repeat with the other half of the dough. Cook till done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Empty broccoli into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix soup, eggs, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli, but do not mix.
Top with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place margarine, milk and sugar in pan; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted; pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: grandma's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs and sugar together in a large bowl.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture; blend well.
Stir in zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased pans and bake 1 hour.
Remove and cool on cake rack about 10 minutes before turning out.
Cuts better when cool. Bread freezes well if wrapped tightly for up to 6 months.

title: french onion soup
directions: Combine everything, except cheese and croutons.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Cover the bottom of a soup bowl with cheese and croutons and pour soup over.

title: chicken cheddar broccoli
directions: In large skillet brown chicken breasts in margarine for 10 minutes.
Drain grease.
Add soup, broccoli, pepper and water. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce to simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over white rice.
Garnish with tomatoes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box, using milk.
Put one layer of crackers in bottom of pan, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat. Pour cherries over top.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour.
Ready to serve.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add other ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Put rye bread on cookie sheet and spoon mixture onto bread.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw and place under broiler until brown.
Like individual pizzas!
Makes 60 to 70.

title: barbecued minute steaks
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery; drain and put in large pot.
Add remaining ingredients, except meat.
Simmer 1/2 hour, then add drained and broken up or strips of sauteed minute steaks. Simmer another 1/2 hour.
Serve on hoagie rolls or hard rolls with pickles.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Combine the softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 egg and almond extract.
Set aside.
Melt chocolate and butter.
Cool. Beat 2 eggs and 1 cup sugar together.
Add chocolate mixture. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt. Add to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Pour half of the chocolate batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Spread with cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kentucky bourbon balls
directions: Stir together the bourbon and syrup;

thoroughly stir in the remaining ingredients. Spoon 1/2 tablespoon of the mixture onto wax paper, generously covered with extra confectioners sugar. Roll each into a ball; roll in the sugar on the paper. Refrigerate in a tightly covered container at least overnight before serving.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Pour off fat.
Stir in salsa and bouillon.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place bread shell on a large baking sheet.
Top with salsa mixture, cheese, sliced peppers and olives.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese melts.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pizza.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in blender or food processor (10 cookies at a time works best).
Make sure cookies are fine as dirt.

title: garden pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on greased jelly roll or cookie sheet to form crust.
Bake as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise or salad dressing, cream cheese (light works, too!) and seasoning with beater.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle toppings over cream cheese.
Press toppings lightly into cream cheese.
Refrigerate. Cut into squares to serve.

title: green bean beef stew
directions: Have the meat cut in 1-inch cubes; coated with seasoned flour. Heat the drippings in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven; add onions and cook until yellow; add the meat and brown on all sides; add the tomatoes, peeled and quartered, and boiling water.
Cover and simmer gently over low heat, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and continue cooking until meat and beans are tender.
If desired you may remove meat and vegetables.
Thicken gravy and return meat and vegetables to gravy.

title: shirred lemon eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Liberally butter four ramekins.
Pour 1 tablespoon cream in the bottom of each ramekin.
Sprinkle about 1/4 teaspoon lemon zest over the cream in each.
Divide the cheese evenly among the 4 ramekins, sprinkling on top of cream.
Gently drop an egg in each ramekin.
Add salt and pepper.
Measure 1 tablespoon cream and spread over each egg; scatter a little parsley over the tops.
Bake for about 12 minutes or until egg is slightly set.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add other ingredients and simmer for about 1 hour.
Spoon on sandwich buns.

title: do ahead sausage fondue
directions: Grease 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cut bread into cubes.
Place layer on bottom of pan.
Cook and drain sausage; place on layer of bread.
Layer grated cheese on sausage.
Mix together eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: six-flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture with milk.
Stir in flavoring.
Spoon in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Mix all ingredients and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chocolate and stir until melted.

Remove from heat and stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese; beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and spread in lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm.
"Free."

title: banana poppy seed dressing
directions: In a small bowl, finely mash banana.
Add sour cream, sugar, poppy seed, lemon juice, mustard and salt.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Arrange salad greens and fruit on a platter.
Or serve greens in individual salad bowls.
Serve with dressing.
This is a nice dressing to use up that banana that we always find has gotten too ripe to eat.

title: arroz con pollo(rice with chicken)
directions: Rinse chicken with cold water; pat dry.
Add oil to a 12-inch skillet.
Add chicken and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove chicken; drain on paper towels.
Wipe skillet with a paper towel; coat with Pam cooking spray and add chicken to skillet.
Combine water and next 6 ingredients; pour over chicken. Cover and cook over medium heat 15 minutes.
Add rice; cover and cook over medium heat 20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in olives.
Sprinkle with lime juice.

title: low-fat seafood gumbo
directions: Spread flour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° about 45 minutes, stirring once.
Meanwhile in a large saucepan, stir water, onion, pepper, garlic and bouillon to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Cook rice according to directions, omitting butter and salt.
Keep warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Add to salad, toss again and serve.

title: orange dessert
directions: Drain Mandarin oranges and pineapple well.
Save juice for another use.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Very good!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
This can be made and frozen for 2 weeks.

title: microwaved strawberry jam
directions: In a 2-quart glass container, microwave frozen strawberries on High for 2 minutes. Stir in pectin and microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir in sugar and lemon juice.
Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring after first 3 minutes.
Pour into glass jars. Cool to room temperature, cover and refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom.
Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pan and bake 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: zuppa toscanna soup
directions: Cook sausage in a 300° oven. Bake approximately 1/2 hour. Drain on paper towels and cut into slices. Place onions, potatoes, chicken broth, water and garlic in a pot and cook on medium heat until potatoes are done. Add sausage, bacon, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for another 10 minutes. Turn to low heat; add kale and cream. Heat through and serve.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into cubes and put in a baking dish.
Heat milk until hot.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Mix with cold milk.
Pour at once into flour.
Stir lightly with fork until blended.
Add more liquid if necessary to make dough hold together.
Divide into 2 portions.
Refrigerate until ready to prepare pie.
Makes 1 crust.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 11 pieces. Wash thoroughly.
Place chicken in a large bowl. Cover with cold water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours. Drain. Sprinkle with salt again, if desired and lots of black pepper.
In another bowl, place flour. Add dash of salt, black pepper and ground red pepper.
Mix thoroughly.

title: ham delight
directions: Mix ham, noodles and broccoli in a pot. Pour alfredo sauce over top; milk may be added. Great with rolls.

title: ricotta cheese pancakes
directions: In a blender jar, combine Ricotta, eggs, salad oil, flour, sugar and salt.
Cover and blend until smooth; push ingredients from sides of blender or food processor with rubber spatula.
Pour batter in about 3-inch rounds on a lightly greased griddle or wide frying pan over medium-low heat.
Turn cakes with a spatula when bubbles form on the surface.
When browned lightly on both sides, remove from pan.
Keep warm until all are cooked.
To make ahead, cool pancakes or wire racks, then to reheat, place in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Cover and bake 5 minutes at 375°. Serve with fruit and powdered sugar.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain pineapple; put in bowl and mix in whipped topping, walnuts, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Put mixture in graham cracker crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter or oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, then layer coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch bits. Spread condensed milk over the top and sprinkle with nuts. Press lightly. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until well blended.
Add egg and applesauce and blend well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add raisins and rolled oats to flour mixture.
Blend creamed and flour mixtures well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: leslie's cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and form a ball.
Roll cheese ball in chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cut Crisco into dry ingredients. Slightly beat egg and blend it into Milnot. Mix liquid mixture into dry ingredients and stir with large fork or with hands until mixed well. Shape into large ball and pinch off about golf ball size pieces or larger, depending on how large you want to make your pies. Roll out thin and put about a tablespoon of filling on one side; fold over and crimp the sides. Cook in hot cooking oil until brown; turn and brown other side. Cool on rack or paper towel.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place frozen potatoes in a large bowl.
Add melted butter, stirring to coat all potatoes.
Add soup, sour cream, onions, grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: hot chicken salad(yields 4 servings)
directions: Use leftover roast beef and gravy.
Put sliced roast beef and gravy on 2 slices of toast.
Serve with mashed potatoes and sliced tomatoes.

title: fried grits
directions: Cook the grits in 4 times as much water.
Boil several minutes and stir in a heaping tablespoon of flour.
Remove from fire and stir in egg, mixing thoroughly.
Add just enough water to make consistency of pancake batter.
Spoon into hot (375°) grease in size of small pancakes.
Brown on both sides.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add cream cheese.
Stir in
nuts and a small can of Carnation cream.
Chill and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in oil until tender.
Add meat and cook.
Drain.
Add chili powder and tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir in rice and salt. Turn into a shallow baking dish, sprinkle cheese over top and put under broiler for a few minutes until hot throughout.
Serves 6.

title: easy pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix the oil, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, flour and baking powder all together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Drain the pineapple and put on dough.
Cream the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Add the 5 eggs and 2 tablespoons dry pudding and pour over the pineapple.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: pasta chicken primavera
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in margarine. Remove. Saute mushrooms until tender in same skillet.
In a large saucepan, prepare pasta as directed. Drain. Slice chicken into chunks. Combine chicken, sour cream, mushrooms and pasta mixture.
May be served hot or cold.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast and pull off bone.
Drain corn and put in bottom of pan, put chicken over corn, heat soup and sour cream together and pour over corn and chicken.
Crumble crackers over top, as many as you want (approximately 2 packages).
Melt butter and pour over and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in Dutch oven.
Remove and crumble brown beef in drippings.
Pour off fat.
Add crumbled bacon, broth, wine, garlic and thyme.
Cook in oven over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add onions, carrots and mushrooms.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together the sugar, salt and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Stirring constantly, pour mixture into 2 cups scalded milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Line 9 x 13-inch dish on bottom and sides with vanilla wafers (whole).
Slice bananas and layer on top of wafers. Spread hot pudding over all.
Crumble some wafers and sprinkle on top.

title: one pan mexican style beef bake
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and eggs in greased baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch) with fork until uniform color (batter will be lumpy).

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid. Set liquid aside. Remove skin and bones from salmon. Combine cracker crumbs and reserved liquid. Let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Stir in salmon, corn meal and the next 3 ingredients. Shape salmon mixture into patties. Pour oil into skillet about 1/4-inch deep. Fry patties in hot oil over medium heat until browned, turning once. Drain on paper towels.

title: carol anderson's peach pie
directions: Mix and let set 15 minutes.
Pour into pie crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with pie crust and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: patra's favorite pie crust
directions: Place flour in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Sprinkle with water and stir with fork until it cleans sides of the bowl.
Shape into a ball.
Remove from bowl and place on floured board.
Flatten dough.
Roll out into a thin circle.
Fold into quarters.
Place into pie pan, unfold.
Trim outer edges to within 1 inch of the edge of the pie plate.
Turn under edge and finish edge as desired.
Prick sides and bottom thoroughly.
Bake 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add your favorite filling.
Makes 1 single pie crust.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in heavy saucepan and cook until thick (3 or 4 minutes). Cool.
Knead on wax paper about 5 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Rainy day fun.

title: yogurt soup(from iran)
directions: Beat yogurt and cucumber until smooth.
Blend in water until mixture is consistency of cream soup.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir in raisins, chives and other herbs.
Chill. Just before serving, garnish with egg slices.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer.

title: cranberry meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and milk in a large bowl.
Add meat, oats, onion and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 5 individual loaves and place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over loaves.
Reserve glaze for basting.
Bake about 45 minutes, basting once or twice with glaze.
Serve remaining glaze warm in gravy boat.

title: sausages
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain off fat.
Mix hamburger, hot sausage, chili powder, garlic powder, and cheese, Cook until melted.
Place 1 Tbsp. of mixture on Party Rye Slices.
Bake at 350 until crispy.

title: country chicken stew saute
directions: Wipe chicken dry; season with salt and pepper and dust lightly with flour.
In a large frying pan over medium heat, saute chicken in butter until golden on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Add bacon and saute until golden.
Add onion and mushrooms and saute until limp.
Return chicken to the pan along with the potatoes, brandy, water, lemon peel, bay leaf, thyme and garlic.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until the potatoes and chicken are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with juices spooned over.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs in mushroom soup
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, salt and pepper. Shape into balls. Place in skillet and brown. Drain off fat. Add water and mushroom soup.
Mix well and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: mona's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until smooth.
Bake in 2 well-greased pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: aunt ruby's peanut butter icing
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring salt, sugar, milk and butter to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Set pan in cold water and beat, adding 2 or 3 tablespoons peanut butter.
For more than 2 layers, double recipe.

title: peanut butter milk shake
directions: Pour milk into blender container.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Blend at high speed 15 seconds or until smooth.
(Mixture thickens as it stands.
Thin with additional milk, if desired.) Makes 3 large or 5 small servings.

title: cauliflower in butter
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets and then into little pieces.
Place cauliflower in boiling salt water and cook until tender. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain again and dredge with seasoned flour.
Pan-fry in butter until lightly browned. Serve with melted butter and parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese log
directions: Pace cream cheese, olives, onions and dried beef in a bowl. Mix with your hands thoroughly.
Sprinkle Accent into the mixture and work it in good.
Do this several times.
Take a portion and make a log shape.
Place it in a serving tray.
This will make 3 logs.
Sprinkle Accent over the tray lightly.

title: hot chili
directions: Brown meat; add onions, then add remaining ingredients over slow fire.
Add water and can of tomatoes with juice.
Cook slowly for 2 hours making sure it does not stick.
Call the fire department.

title: spaetzle dumplings
directions: In a medium bowl mix all ingredients together.
Prepare a firm dough.
Beat until it comes easily away from the sides of the bowl.
With a spoon press the dough through a dumpling sifter into salted boiling water.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Skim them out and dip in cold water.
Spaetzle dumplings can be also browned lightly in butter before serving and they are my favorite accompaniment to meat with sauce.

title: oven butter-browned potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and dry with paper towels.
In oven, melt butter in 2-quart baking dish. Roll potatoes in butter to coat thoroughly.
Arrange in dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.
Turn potatoes. Spoon remaining butter over potatoes.
Continue to bake, uncovered, 45 minutes until browned.

title: bread dough (modeling dough)
directions: Shred bread, then add white glue.
Work until dough forms (will be very gooey at first, then very smooth).
Dough when dry may be painted.
Shape into miniature flowers, etc.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix brownies according to directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in cooled brownies and pour topping in.
Mix pudding according to directions for chocolate mousse.
Break up 1/2 pan of brownies and layer in large clear bowl.
Cover with 1/2 mousse mixture, 1/2 container of Cool Whip and 1/2 the crushed bars.
Repeat layers, ending with bars.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Spread cranberries on bottom of a buttered 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Beat eggs until thick and gradually add granulated sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Add flour and butter and beat well.
Pour batter over cranberries and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Combine water, oil and 2 cups flakes.
Beat sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients including remaining flakes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes on middle rack.
Leftover batter may be stored in tightly closed jar in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: olive garden spinach & artichoke dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Cream together mayonnaise, Parmesan, Romano cheese, garlic, basil and garlic salt. Mix well.
Add the artichoke hearts and spinach (careful to drain this well), and mix until blended.
Store in a container until you are ready to use.
Spray pie pan with PAM, pour in dip and top with cheese.

title: pepperoni angel hair
directions: Cook the pasta according to the directions.
Meanwhile combine the cucumber, green pepper, pepperoni and olives in a large bowl.
Drain pasta and add to the pepperoni mixture.
Top with the salad dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Toss to coat.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan sprayed with Pam.
Spread 1 cup chopped pecans and flaked coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix the oleo and softened cream cheese, then add the powdered sugar.
Mix well until creamed together.
Pour mixture over top of cake mix batter.
Gently take a knife and marble the mixture slightly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix and dissolve jello, sugar and hot water.
Add pineapple juice, lemon and cold water.
Mix well.
Freeze in 3 portions in plastic containers.
Allow at least 2 days to freeze.
When ready to serve, take 1 portion of frozen mixture and put in punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over frozen mixture, then use an ice pick to make a slush mixture.
Repeat with another frozen mixture and ginger ale as needed.

title: baked spaghetti(lo-fat, lo-sugar)
directions: Fry bacon 2 minutes.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until soft. Add ground beef and brown.
Add salt, pepper, chili powder, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in the olives, sliced.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Place on bottom of casserole dish. Mix rice by directions on box and celery soup all together.
Add the remaining ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or freeze and bake later; just allow for thawing.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute chilies in bacon drippings.
Add garlic and flour.
Cook slowly for several minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and cheese.
Heat until melted.

title: pasty-double crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Cut shortening into flour with 2 knives until pieces are about the size of small peas.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix in electric mixer. Divide into 3 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This freezes well.

title: aunt mae's monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix white sugar and cinnamon in a large plastic bag.
Shake 6 to 8 biscuit quarters in mixture. Arrange in well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins among biscuits.
Melt butter and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tomato and feta cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss gently and refrigerate covered for at least 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup nuts.
Mix well.
Roll in the remaining 1/2 cup of nuts.
Makes 1 large or 2 small balls. This can be frozen.

title: fiesta mexican casserole
directions: Cook rice. Cook beef, onion, salt, pepper and garlic.

Drain. Mix chilies, soup, milk, Ro-Tel, enchilada sauce and cheese in bowl. Add meat and rice to the mixture and stir. Layer chips in bottom of pan and pour mixture on top. Top with chips and cheese. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain lima beans and kidney beans.
Layer one row of pork and beans in bean pot with 1/3 of chopped onion, 1 1/2 tablespoons of brown sugar and 3 tablespoons ketchup.
Repeat for other beans. Put strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: lisa's chicken pie
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place chicken on bottom of dish.
Mix soups and broth and pour over chicken.
Scatter peas and carrots. Mix milk and melted butter.
Add a little bit of flour and baking powder at a time to the milk and margarine.
(Whisk smooth while adding.)
Pour over soup layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Crust will bake up to top and brown.
This recipe was given to me by my daughter, Lisa.
It's a great recipe and I think you'll enjoy it.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, then melted margarine and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fried shrimp batter
directions: Combine flour, salt, egg, oil and water to make batter and roll shrimp in extra flour before frying.

title: chewy bread
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients and mix well. Spray cooking spray in bottom of a 13 x 9 inch pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool before cutting.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Set aside. Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.

title: green vegetable and egg salad
directions: Cook each frozen vegetable separately following package directions.
Drain well.
Combine all vegetables and toss them lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon egg mixture over vegetables; stir gently.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: orange refrigerator cookies (no bake)
directions: In large bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar, nuts, butter or margarine and orange juice concentrate.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
(If crumb mixture is soft, refrigerate before shaping balls.)
Roll balls in coconut.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Yields 70 to 80 small balls.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix batter until fairly thick.
Let rise and work down to biscuit dough.
Cut out with a small cutter.
Put in roll pan and let rise until double; bake in a 350° oven.

title: peach cobber
directions: Wash and slice peaches. Combine sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in pan.
Add peaches and lemon juice. Add enough water to almost cover the peaches. Cook on medium until peaches are tender. If peaches are tart, 1/3 cup extra sugar may be added.

title: orange gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and brown sugar with Crisco and butter.
Add eggs. Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together and add to butter mixture.
Add gumdrops, nuts and vanilla; stir well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: 1 minute chocolate sauce
directions: Mix together in small saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
May be doubled.
May be made into fudge by boiling longer.

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and drain grease, add remaining ingredients, bring to a boil then simmer over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: dill dip with dill bread
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream, dried onion, season salt, mayonnaise, dillweed and salt.
Chill in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Cut a 6-inch circle from top of round bread loaf.
Set aside circle to use as a lid.
Remove bread inside of loaf in small bite size pieces.
Put crust shell on a serving tray and put chilled dip inside loaf.
Arrange bread pieces around loaf to serve.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken artichoke casserole
directions: Sprinkle the breasts with parsley, salt, pepper and a dash of garlic powder.
Roll secure and saute until golden brown.
Place cooked rolled breasts in a large buttered casserole dish.
Add drained artichoke hearts (break in 1/2).

title: peanut butter incredibles
directions: Mix graham crackers and powdered sugar together.
Add melted butter and peanut butter to cracker mixture. Mix real well with hands.
Press cracker mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt all chips together and pour over top of cracker mixture.
Let cool. Cut before chocolate becomes too hard.

title: party sausage rye
directions: Fry sausage in heavy skillet over medium heat and stir to break up.
Pour off grease, add cheese and lower heat.
Stir until cheese melts and blends with sausage.
Spread on party rye and broil until lightly browned, or freeze until ready to use.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage covered in a small amount of boiling salted water about 5 minutes; drain.
Combine sour cream or yogurt with seasonings and toss with cabbage and heat through.
Do not boil. Makes 4 servings.

title: bean-burger casserole
directions: Brown bacon.
Drain excess fat.
Add hamburger and continue to simmer.
Add mustard, onion, catsup, vinegar and brown sugar. Simmer and stir until done.
Add butter beans and kidney beans (drain before adding).
Add pork and beans, including the sauce. Stir well and transfer to casserole.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease three No. 2 or 303 size cans or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Chop nuts and mash the bananas.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt. Combine butter, sugar, eggs and flavoring in mixing bowl. Cream for 1 1/2 minutes. Add bananas, sour cream, nuts and flour mixture.
Beat until well blended. Fill cans about 2/3 full. Bake 1 hour or until done.
Let stand several minutes, then remove from cans.
Cool thoroughly before serving.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground meat, drain.
Add the next 7 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to an hour.
Stir often.
Cook noodles in lightly salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt, Parmesan cheese, pepper and parsley.
Stack half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half of cottage cheese mixture on this, add 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese, then half of meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 335° for 30 minutes.

title: filling balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well;
shape into balls.
