Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: fried okra and squash
directions: Mix the
okra,	squash	and onions; salt and pepper the mixture.
Combine
and
beat
the egg and buttermilk.
Dip the vegetable mixture
in the egg and buttermilk.
Drain.
Mix the flour and meal together in a separate bowl.
Batter the dipped vegetable mixture in the meal and flour.
Deep fry to a golden brown.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add 1/4 cup sugar, gelatin, salt and milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until blended.
Cool. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold into cooled peanut butter mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in large bowl and mix well. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to serve.
Place lettuce leaf and tomato slice in each pita bread.
Spoon chicken salad on top of lettuce and tomato. Garnish with green grapes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar. Let stand for few minutes.
Stir together 2 cups flour, yeast and salt.
Add liquid ingredients and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add enough additional flour to make soft, yet manageable, dough (about 2 1/2 cups).
Knead 8 to 10 minutes until smooth.
Divide dough into 12 equal portions and roll each section into 15-inch rope.
Roll lightly in coarse salt or topping of choice and shape into pretzel.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.
Upon removing from oven, brush with melted butter liberally on both sides.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans together and pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust.
Prepare chocolate pudding with milk until thick and spread over second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with sweet chocolate shavings.
Chill.

title: inside-out chocolate cake
directions: Combine pudding mix, cake mix, milk and eggs in large bowl; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into greased 12-cup Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan for 30 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Yields 16 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Use Sweet Roll Dough recipe.
After dough rises, roll into oblong shape.
Spread with mixture of butter, sugar and cinnamon. Roll up tightly, beginning at wide side.
Seal well.
Stretch roll slightly to even.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place a little apart in greased pan.
Cover and let rise until double (35 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stew beef as pot roast
directions: Grease casserole; brown meat in oil.
Add 3 cups water and 1 cup wine to meat mixture.
Add dried onion soup, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Add cream of mushroom soup to casserole; continue to bake, covered, for 30 minutes to 1 hour, until meat is cooked and tender.
This makes a great meal served over rice or with egg noodles, boiled and buttered.

title: beef biscuit
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and gravy in one pan
directions: Coat chicken with flour (13 x 9-inch pan).
Arrange chicken in melted butter in pan skin down. Bake, uncovered in 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken bake 15 to 20 minutes longer until brown.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat.

title: elegant 'n easy company dessert
directions: Line a buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil. Leave 1 1/2-inches overhang on all sides.
Butter foil.
Arrange 8 ladyfinger halves over bottom and sides of pan.
Toast almonds in 2 tablespoons butter over low heat until golden brown, stirring constantly. Drain and cool.
Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Cream the butter until soft.
Continue beating and add sugar-cocoa mixture. Slowly add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well. Fold in nuts and whipped cream. Spread 1/3 of the chocolate mixture over ladyfingers.
Repeat twice.
Chill 4 hours. Slice and serve with whipped cream.
Makes 12 to 20 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together. Add the egg and beat well. Stir in the bananas and then the dry ingredients. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 24 hour layer salad
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish with lettuce.
Sprinkle with peppers.
Add layer of celery, then layer of onion and layer of frozen peas.
Combine rest of the ingredients.
Combine rest of ingredients and put on top, then sprinkle top with cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
No cooking; no salt.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown bacon.
Cook onion, celery with garlic and basil until tender.
Stir in soups, water, tomatoes, macaroni and salt.
Bring to boil, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and zucchini; cook 10 minutes more until done.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 8 cups.

title: tuna vegetable souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water, vinegar, mayonnaise,
salt
and
pepper. Blend well with rotary beater. Refrigerate
until	partially congealed, about the consistency of honey.
Whip
until
fluffy.
Fold	in vegetables and tuna. Pour into
cup mold.	Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serves about 10 people.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: In small bowl, soak bread crumbs in milk, about 5 minutes.
In large bowl, combine meats, egg, salt, pepper, allspice and breadcrumb mixture; toss gently with fork just to combine.
Using hands shape into 30 meat balls.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute meat balls, half at a time, until they are browned and cooked all the way through, about 10 minutes.
Remove meat balls as they are cooked and place in large bowl.
Remove skillet from heat; add flour to drippings in skillet, stirring until smooth.
Add bouillon cube, then stir in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring until bouillon is dissolved and mixture is smooth.
Add cream and milk; simmer gently, stirring 3 minutes. Add meat balls to sauce; toss gently to coat well.
Cool quickly, then cover and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, reheat gently. Sprinkle with dill.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening.
Cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to mixture.
Chill.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Allow to sit at room temperature for 15 minutes before forming balls.

title: curried yams
directions: Peel yams if you wish.
Cut in chunks.
Eggplant may be substituted for some of the yams.
Simmer butter, garlic and ginger 5 minutes.
Add herbs and spices; simmer.
Add milk; simmer.
Squeeze 1 1/2 lemons to curdle the milk.
Add to vegetables or use sauce for other curry dishes.
Increase cayenne for a hotter curry.
Serve with yogurt and condiments (nuts, coconut, banana, chutney, raisins, etc.).

title: old fashion dumplings
directions: Combine flour, broth and oil; stir until moist.
Divide in 3 balls, sprinkle flour on top.
Roll them, cut in strips.
Place in hot broth and cook 15 minutes or until tender.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Stir in 1/2 cup white sugar, egg yolks, flour and nuts.
Last fold in egg whites.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix marinade ingredients well.
Cut cauliflower, carrots and celery into bite-size pieces.
Combine all ingredients in large container (at least 3 qt.).
Refrigerate and marinate 24 hrs. tossing frequently.
You could also add whole button mushrooms.

title: yummy carrot salad
directions: Wash carrots, apples and celery. Grate carrots into salad bowl. Add raisins. Chop apples, celery and nuts and add to salad bowl. Combine mayo, salt, sugar and lemon juice. Mix well. Add to Salad bowl, mixing well. Serve on top of lettuce leaves. Sprinkle extra raisins and nuts on top if you wish.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, & eggs together. Add flour a little at a time. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased pan real thin. Bake at 325 until light brown.

title: venison pork meat loaf
directions: Mix all well and add enough milk to make moist.
Shape into a loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter brickle bars
directions: Mix together dry cake mix and oleo.
Add slightly beaten egg. Mix all together to form a soft ball of dough.
Press into greased jelly roll pan.
Drizzle canned milk (Borden Eagle Brand) over the entire top.
Sprinkle on nuts and chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: impossible punkin pie
directions: Place in blender.
Mix on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Allow to cool and serve with whipped topping.

title: pear anise pie
directions: Or you can use just a regular pie crust.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Remove crusts from all bread.
Roll each slice flat and very thin.
Mix Blue Cheese, mayonnaise, egg and cream cheese.
Spread on each slice of bread.
Put 1 spear of asparagus.
Roll up and slice.
Dip each piece in butter.
Freeze.
Brown in 350° oven till brown.

title: egg omelette hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients in a glass baking dish and bake in oven 14 minutes at medium setting.
Cut into squares while hot and serve on Triscuits or your favorite cracker.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in dish.
Put mayonnaise and sugar on top.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl, except chocolate chips.
Mix by hand; do not use mixer.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° about 50 minutes.
Check it at 35 minutes.
Can use tube or long pan.

title: our favorite rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk and add butter, sugar and salt.
Mix well and let it cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Mix in eggs and yeast.
Beat well. Gradually add enough flour to make a soft dough, beating well. Cover and let it rise in a warm place until double in size.
Push it down and with lightly greased hands, shape into rolls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let them rise until double in size.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroon pie(serves 8)
directions: Beat egg whites, adding 1/2 cup sugar; beat until stiff.
Beat 1/2 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Add rest of ingredients (crumbs, nuts, extract and salt).
Fold into egg whites.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cover with whipped cream.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove from bone and cut in small pieces. Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a saucepan, mix and bring to a boil soup and broth.
In a bowl, mix melted margarine, pepper, flour and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly to form a batter.
Pour broth and soup mixture over chicken.
Add peas and spoon the batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of onion soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: creamy crock-pot potatoes
directions: Toss potato slices in 1 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar. Drain and put half of potatoes in greased crock-pot. Top with half of onion, flour, salt and pepper.

Layer with potatoes and onion, salt, pepper and flour again. Pour soup and butter on top. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours or on high 2 to 4 hours. Add 4 slices American cheese to top 30 minutes before serving.

title: carrot casserole almondine
directions: Boil carrots in water with salt until tender-crisp; drain. Place carrots, tomatoes and herbs in a 1-quart buttered casserole. Mix crushed cheese crackers and almonds with melted butter and use to top casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be made early in the day and reheated.
Serves 4.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until nearly done.
Peel and slice into large baking dish.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars and margarine in a large bowl. Stir in pumpkin, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except frosting and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool.
Mix frosting and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; frost cookies.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican hot sauce
directions: Blend ingredients in blender. Add honey
to taste.
Adjust cayenne according to heat desired, 3 teaspoons is real hot!!! Refrigerate.

title: tuna jackstraw casserole
directions: Reserve 1 cup of potatoes for topping.
Combine remaining potatoes with other ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Put remaining potatoes on top and bake at 375°, uncovered, for 25 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Heat sour cream to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar, soda and salt. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add egg, shortening and flour.
Knead gently.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Roll into an oblong, 24 x 6-inches.
Spread with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle half lengthwise with mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon. Fold other half over.
Cut into 3/4-inch strips and twist each strip.
Place on greased baking sheet pressing both ends of twists to baking sheet.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 hour. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost, when cool, with mixture of powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons butter, extract and 1 to 2 tablespoons warm water.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk and pudding mix into a medium bowl.
Beat with a wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Gently stir in whipped topping and half of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon of crushed cookies in bottom of 8 ounce plastic or paper cups; fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
If desired, decorate with gummy worms or gumdrop flowers to resemble flower pots.
Refrigerate for one hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chalupas
directions: Brown meat and 1 onion (chopped).
Sprinkle with flour, salt and chili powder.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

Combine milk, soup, cheese and other chopped onion. Slice tortillas into one inch strips and line greased baking dish with strips. Alternate with layers of beef and cheese mixture, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: moist and fruity rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean layer pans.
Prick each layer with a serving fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and pour carefully over cakes.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Dip 1 cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Turn out onto serving plate.
Top with 1 cup of Cool Whip. Unmold second layer and place carefully on top of first layer.
Frost top and sides with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine soup mix, sour cream, curry powder and vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with potato chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: purple plum upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and flour to smooth paste.
Stir in lemon juice and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put plums, cut side down, on top of paste.
Mix cake mix with remaining ingredients.
Spread over plums.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: double fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in heavy saucepan.
Stir in water and corn syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full, over-all boil.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in evaporated milk and vanilla.
Serve cold or warm over cake, pudding or ice cream.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a large skillet; drain.
Add all ingredients and stir to mix.
Mix on low heat for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: french donuts
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, the yeast and nutmeg.
Combine milk, sugar, oil and salt; heat until warm.
Add to dry ingredients and add egg.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute. Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in greased bowl and turn once. Cover and chill.
Place dough on lightly floured surface, cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Roll dough to 18 x 12-inch rectangle. Cut into donut shapes.
Cover again and let rise 30 minutes.
Fry in deep hot (375°) oil until golden, turning once.
Drain and dip into glaze.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen donuts.

title: romanian cabbage rolls
directions: Cut off core end of cabbage and pick out 15 of the largest leaves.
Set the rest aside.
In a large pot, cook the leaves for about 2 minutes in boiling salted water.
It's easiest to cook 4 to 5 leaves at once instead of all at one time.
Drain and cool.
Heat oil and butter in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add onions, garlic and then mushrooms.
After mushrooms are well coated, add paprika.
Stir occasionally until soft and most the juice is gone. Stir in rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cook 1 more minute.
Remove from heat and add cheese.
Spoon onto each leaf. Tuck sides over and roll to enclose.
Put in baking dish, seams down.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Make cornbread according to package instructions. Chop sausage in food processor. Fry and drain. Saute bell pepper, onion and green onions in butter. Add squash and cook until tender. Add sausage and cheese. Cook until cheese melts. Add sugar and Creole seasoning. Mix in crumbled cornbread. Place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° until hot. Serves 8.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and egg.
Add the buttermilk and blend.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add them to the buttermilk mixture.
Stir in the raisins.
Bake in a greased 8-inch or 9-inch round cake pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Sprinkle lightly with sugar before baking.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Combine the margarine, milk and cocoa.
Boil or microwave until bubbling.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on cake while hot.

title: 5 pound chocolate fudge
directions: Put first five ingredients in a very large bowl.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Alternate fruit and cucumber on 5-inch skewers.
Heat jelly until melted.
Stir in water and poppy seed.
Refrigerate kabobs and sauce separately.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: rice sausage chicken casserole
directions: Brown sausage with pepper, onion and celery.
Brown until clear, not brown.
Add rice.
Cook very slowly one hour (simmer). Stir often.
I usually stand over stove.
Then cook soup in water. Cook for 10 minutes and gradually add this to meat and rice mixture.
Continue to stir.
Add water chestnuts.
Put in casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
If casserole appears dry, I add some clear chicken broth from a can or some I might have from baking a chicken.

title: popsicles
directions: You will also need paper cups and popsicle sticks.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion until brown.
Add beef; stir until brown.
Boil pasta per package directions.
Drain and add to beef mixture.
Toss well.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika for color.
Bake until cheese melts (about 5 minutes) in 350° oven or 1 to 2 minutes under broiler.

title: italian chicken
directions: Saute onions in olive oil.
Add chicken and fry until done. Drain off oil.
Prepare wine, garlic, tomato sauce and rosemary and pour over chicken.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: broiled fish(pesce alla griglia)
directions: Preheat
broiler.
Wash
fish
thoroughly
under
cold water. Pat dry and place on
broiler pan that has been rubbed with oil. Cut two 1-inch slits
on
each side of fish.
Whisk together vinegar, garlic,
lemon
juice,
parsley,
olive oil, salt and pepper.
With leafy
top
of
celery, baste fish with vinegar mixture.
Place under hot
broiler
and broil 10 to 15 minutes per side, basting often.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Stir 1 to 3 rounded teaspoonfuls into 1 cup boiling water. Excellent for diabetics.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sift together into first mixture the flour, baking powder, soda and spices.
Stir to blend.
Add nuts/raisins.
Beat about 4 minutes.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: heart healthy snack mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a paper bag. Add oil, dill and seasoning. Shake until well mixed.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Put gelatin in bowl and pour water or juice over it.
Let soak a few minutes.
Pour boiling water in bowl and stir until completely dissolved.
Add cut up marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Set in cold place until thick, then add 1 cup nuts, 1 cup mayo, 2 packages cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups crushed pineapple.
Store in fridge for 8 hours.
Serves 12.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, beat together butter and sugar until light and creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Beat in flour and baking powder until well blended. Divide into 4 pieces. Wrap each in plastic and let cool about 1 hour in refrigerator or until firm. On lightly floured area, roll out dough with floured rolling pin about 1-inch. Cut out shapes. Bake 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Cool and decorate.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole(good for a crowd!)
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cut chicken in large bite-size pieces and layer over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo, lemon and sherry and pour over broccoli and chicken. Then sprinkle with cheese.
Then sprinkle with crumbs.
Then sprinkle with butter (melted).
Bake, covered, at 350°, about 1 hour until bubbly and very hot.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl 3 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm, stirring until shortening melts.
Add to dry mixture in mixing bowl and beat 3 minutes. Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape into a ball; place dough in lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch down and knead for 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls or loaf pans.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double, 60 minutes or more.
Bake in oven about 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove from pans to cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 dozen rolls or 2 or 3 loaves.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes and margarine together.
Add sugar, salt, spices and flavorings.
Separate eggs.
Blend yolks with milk (add more milk if desired); add to potato mixture (will be a very thin consistency).
Pour into unbaked pie shell; cook at 400° until lightly browned (approximately 45 minutes).

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Mix eggs, sugars and butter in mixing bowl.
Beat one minute.
Add sifted flour, chopped nuts and vanilla, mixing well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
When done, inside will be moist.
Store in container with tight lid.
Cut into squares or bars while warm.

title: rice with chicken broth
directions: Heat oil in heavy lidded saucepan.
Add rice and onion and cook slowly, until onion is transparent and rice is opaque and both are golden, but not brown.
Remove from heat.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer lettuce, cauliflower and onion.
Mix mustard in Miracle Whip and spread over top of vegetables. Sprinkle sugar over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over that. Sprinkle bacon bits over the top, if desired.
Refrigerate in layers and toss just before serving.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients with grated cabbage and chill.
Creamy Italian dressing or mayonnaise can also be used to taste.

title: cranberry raspberry mold
directions: Spray mold with Pam.
Mix 1 box jello and cream cheese with 1 cup boiling water.
Pour into mold; let set about 1 1/2 hours. Mix other box of jello with 1 cup hot water.
Add cranberry sauce. Pour over first layer.
Let jell.

title: beef on toast
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain off fat.
Melt oleo in frypan.
Add flour and cook until bubbly.
Add milk and stir; cook until thick. Season with salt and pepper.
You may add 2 boiled eggs that have been cut up to the sauce.
Serve on toast.

title: almond butter crunch candy
directions: Place almonds on a cookie sheet; toast in moderate 375° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly golden.
Combine butter, sugar, corn syrup and water in a medium-sized heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 300° on candy thermometer.
A teaspoon of syrup will separate into brittle threads when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup toasted almonds. Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spreading quickly and evenly.
Cool.
Turn out onto wax paper.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large skillet.
Add rest of ingredients.
Turn into a greased casserole dish and top with corn bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bread is done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 1 or 2 buttered casserole dishes.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 20.

title: t-ring
directions: Grease a Bundt cake pan.
Arrange by layers alternately. Start with bread, 1/2 package of pudding, 1/2 brown sugar, 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Repeat, putting bread halfway on top of each other.
Let rise.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes. Let cool.
Turn over on foil.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Slightly brown ground beef, then add the remaining ingredients and bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 400° oven.
It will be brown on top.

title: convenience casserole
directions: Into 2-quart casserole, slice potatoes, carrots, celery and onions (salt lightly).
Cover with hamburger which has been lightly browned and seasoned.
Over all pour soup.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: roman holiday
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Saute onion, green pepper and tomatoes, chopping up tomatoes as you saute.
Add hamburger.
Cook on medium 10 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti on top.
Place cheese slices on top of spaghetti.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Prepare in blender.
DO NOT DOUBLE RECIPE!
Make 1 recipe at a time.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut the Crisco into the flour.
Add the water, milk, oil and salt.
Mix gradually.
Work into a ball using a little extra flour to handle.
Chill before rolling out.
Keeps well in refrigerator for at least a week.
Makes 3 single crusts.

title: mango sorbet
directions: Combine all ingredients in non-corrosive pan.
Bring to a boil; reduce to simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove to a shallow container; set in freezer.
Stir every 30 minutes to keep from freezing solid.
Scrape into glasses; garnish with raspberry sauce and fresh mint.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place diced, cooked chicken.
Drain Veg-All and pour over chicken.
Then add cream of chicken and cream of celery soups over the Veg-All.
Mix Bisquick, margarine and milk until well blended.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: new zealand salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and beat well with a whisk or egg beater until the mixture thickens. That's all. It makes a salad dressing which can be stored in the refrigerator for a very long time.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips. Sift together following ingredients: flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat until well combined.
Fill muffin cup 1/3 full with chocolate batter. Top each one with heaping teaspoonful cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients well.
Add the dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: sunset salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill until very thick, then fold in carrots and pecans.
Pour into molds.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: oriental salad dressing
directions: Dressing is best if prepared the night before so it will have time to marinate. Shake it several times that day. Pour dressing over salad when you are ready to serve it; this is necessary. This will keep the salad from becoming soggy.

title: pork chop apple bake
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in bottom of baking dish; place apples slices next.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Next place filling on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raisin spice bars
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together for 20 minutes.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and spread on a greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: baked spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Place spareribs in roasting pan with cover.
Bake, uncovered, in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes.
Remove ribs.
Pour off some of fat.
Put 1 quart sauerkraut in pan; arrange ribs on top and season with salt and pepper.
Pour on 1 cup hot water; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Crust: Flatten crescent rolls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.
Allow to cool.

title: oatmeal and coconut cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Add coconut and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel bread
directions: Thaw bread dough (don't let rise).
Break up loaf in bottom of Bundt pan.
Heat brown sugar, butter, vanilla pudding and milk until dissolved, but don't boil.
Pour over broken chunks and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add broken chunks from other loaf of bread and sprinkle with cinnamon again.
Let rise.

title: old-fashioned iron skillet chocolate pie(good)
directions: In a mixing bowl, sift cocoa, flour and salt together. Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks into cup of milk.
In a large iron skillet, melt margarine.
Add flour mixture and slowly pour beaten egg yolks and milk, stirring constantly.
(Use low heat.)
Cook until mixture is thick and fudge like.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites using 2 to 3 teaspoons sugar until stiff.
Pour over pie and bake until golden in color.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven at 400°; grease pie plate or pan.
Brown beef and onions, drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour over beef mixture in plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean about 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Makes 3 1/2 cups. Drain marinade and use again.
Store in tightly covered jar in freezer indefinitely or in refrigerator for 1 week.
(May reuse once.)
Marinate flank steak overnight, piercing with fork and turning several times.
Slice meat on diagonal (tastes best after being grilled!).

title: potato pierogi
directions: Combine flour, eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water in a mixing bowl.
Mix well to make a medium soft dough.
Knead well until dough is firm.
Cover with a warm towel and let rest 10 minutes.

title: pineapple surprise cake
directions: Mix items together and refrigerate.
Make a yellow cake according to directions.
Cool.
Cut cake in half, lengthways. Spread a layer of Cool Whip mixture on bottom layer of cake. Place top half of cake on that.
Spread remainder of mixture on top (make up like a layer cake).
Refrigerate.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix per box instructions.
While cake is baking, mix the Eagle Brand milk and extract in something with small pour spout.

title: uncle mike's hamburgers
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and form patties.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: taco soup
directions: In crock-pot, melt sour cream, cheese, tomatoes and beans. Add brown ground beef and taco seasoning mix. Season as you like. Serve with nacho chips.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together well.
Dough should not be too stiff.
Drop by teaspoon.

title: "no fail" pancakes
directions: Mix oil, egg and milk together. Mix dry ingredients together. Add both mixtures together. Add 2 more tablespoons of milk. Mix. Fry on hot griddle.

title: ice cream cake(ingredients for 10 servings.)
directions: Grease and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, with electric mixer, cream butter with 1 3/4 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 1 minute.
Add flour mixture alternately with water, beating well after each addition.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan. Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: hot milk cake
directions: With mixer, beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat.
Set aside. Heat milk; add margarine to milk and mix until margarine is melted.
Cool slightly.
Sift flour and baking powder; add alternately with milk to egg and sugar mixture.
Add lemon extract and mix batter well.
Grease and flour angel food or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until nicely brown.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Cook flour and oil in a heavy saucepan over medium heat; stir frequently.
When it begins to brown (after 10 to 15 minutes), stir constantly.
When mixture is a deep reddish-brown (after 10 minutes), add bell pepper, celery and onions.

title: mexican snacks
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When once selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them in hot water.
This makes them sour, hard to get along with and sometimes bitter.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Cut chicken into cubes.
In small bowl, mix salt, mayo, milk and lemon.
In large bowl, mix chicken, grapes, celery, cashews, onion and chilled rice.
Fold in mayo mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Melt oleo, water and peanut butter in saucepan; heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat. Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add the peanut butter mixture; add in eggs and sour milk. Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: santa's fudge
directions: Cook sugar, oleo and milk; bring to boil.
Stir 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate until melted; add creme, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well; pour into buttered pan.

title: poppy seed lemon bread
directions: Beat all ingredients for 5 minutes. Grease and flour your bread pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: tex-mex tortilla stack
directions: Mix chicken, jicama and 1/2 cup taco sauce.
Set aside.
Place one tortilla on a platter.
Spread with half of chicken mixture. Spread half of avocado dip onto second tortilla; place, avocado side up, atop chicken.
Sprinkle with half of the lettuce.
Top with a third tortilla; spread with half of the beans.
Top with another tortilla; add half each of the sour cream, red pepper, green onion and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sour cream, red pepper, green onion and cheese.
Sprinkle with olives.
Serve right away or cover and chill for up to 3 hours.
(It will cut easier if it is chilled.)

title: oyster balls
directions: Cut
oysters
in
pieces.
Break
up saltines.
In a baking dish
or large bowl put 1/3 saltines, 1/3 oysters, 1/3 butter and
parsley.
Repeat
this until you have 3 layers of the mixture.
Drizzle
oyster
juice over all and let sit and marinate for 1 1/2 hours.

title: people puppy chow
directions: You will need 2 paper sacks.

title: western roundup salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin, salt and spices in boiling water.
Add measured liquid and vinegar.
Chill until thickened. Fold in fruit and spoon into 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold.
Garnish as desired.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 cup melted butter, pepper, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, salt, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Place potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Top with corn flakes and other 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: milk shake
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.
Makes approximately 2 servings; each contains 92 calories and less than 1 g fat.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain and reserve liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick. Continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese which has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted.
Combine with cooked spinach.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Add turkey or chicken.
Cut up. Mix together. Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: miniature reuben sandwiches(makes about 15)
directions: Spread the bread slices with the corned beef.
Top each with some of the sauerkraut and a rectangle of cheese.
Cover with remaining bread slices.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring water, sugar and cloves to a boil and let simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags and let steep 5 minutes. Remove tea bags and cloves.
Add juices and stir.
Serve hot. Store in refrigerator.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, breadcrumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce in large mixing bowl, mixing well.
Place mixture in a deep round Pyrex pie plate, around a small glass in center of dish.
Combine remaining tomato sauce and remaining ingredients in small mixing bowl and pour 1/2 over loaf.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over loaf and microwave another 5 minutes.

title: cream tacos
directions: If using corn tortillas, soften in hot oil; drain on paper towels.
Mix together chicken, cheese, green chiles and onion. Fill tortillas with mixture and roll.
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Mix together the soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour over filled tortillas.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook first three ingredients together until dates become very soft; stir constantly.
Add the Rice Krispies and toasted pecans to the date mixture and mix well.
Make into small balls while mixture is warm.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Place butter in oven until it melts.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.

title: old-fashion triple fudge cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured rectangular pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over batter and bake as directed on cake mix box. Immediately after baking, poke deep holes through top of cake (still in pan) with meat fork.
Space holes about 1-inch apart. Spread fudge topping evenly over cake.
Serve when completely cool, topped with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: stuffed celery sticks
directions: Cut celery into 3-inch pieces (make sure celery is dry).
Mix remaining ingredients; spread about 1 tablespoon in each piece of celery.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Makes about 14 appetizers.

title: quick 'n easy bierocks(german sandwiches)
directions: Cook above ingredients until hamburger is done.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large kettle.
Add vinegar gradually stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add vegetables and bring to a boil.
Cook five minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: pumpkin pie dessert squares
directions: Mix and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate peanut butter ice cream sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Serve warm over ice cream or other desserts. Refrigerate leftovers.
Reheat before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: dutch babies
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt the butter in a 400° oven.
In a bowl with wire whisk or eggbeater, beat the eggs, milk and flour. Tilt the melted butter around the sides of a pan; pour in the batter and bake for 20 minutes (it will puff up).
Serve with maple syrup.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Place a little oil in skillet. Brown meat with onion; drain. Add salt, pepper and other seasonings

(use the seasonings you like). Add rice, tomatoes, sauce and water; cook on low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Wash and cut off tops of peppers. Take out seeds. Put in pan and cover with water and bring to a boil. When a knife goes through peppers and they are tender, remove from water and set aside. Put mixture in peppers. (Peppers can be left whole and cut in half.) Sprinkle cheese on top to melt (whatever kind you like).
These can be put in freezer for later when you need something fast. Serve with mashed potatoes and vegetable.

title: creole eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and slice into a bowl of salted water.
Let soak for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour off water and boil eggplant in fresh salted water until very tender; drain and mash.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine, then stir in eggplant, egg, tomatoes, cheese, parsley flakes, baking powder and 1/2 the cracker crumbs.
Mix well, salt to taste and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Hollow out bread loaf.
Mix rest of ingredients and fill hollowed bread with dip.
Take bread pieces, mound together and dip in mix.

title: creole skillet dinner
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Put in chopped onion and chopped bell pepper.
Saute both in the margarine, then add the sausage, the tomato sauce and the vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Enjoy!

title: sandra's beer bread
directions: Mix with spoon all together.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; butter top of bread. Remove from pan.

title: mom's overnight molasses cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Make into 2 rolls on wax paper and place in the refrigerator overnight.
You may need to add a little more flour to handle when making into rolls.
Slice and bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Blend dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; mix until moist.
Add nuts, etc.
Fill greased or Pam sprayed muffin cups almost full.
Bake 17 to 20 minutes.
Turn out on racks to cool.
Preheat oven to 400° to 425°.
Makes 16 to 18 muffins.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Stir Bisquick, milk, sugar, sour cream and eggs until blended.
Add blueberries.
Pour slightly less than 1/4 cup onto hot griddle.
Grease if necessary.
Cook 2 minutes or until pancakes are dry on edge.
Turn and cook another 2 minutes.

title: gorgonzola salad
directions: Mix 1/4 cup oil and garlic in blender.
Rub wooden bowl with mixture.
Tear lettuce; put in bowl with salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Mix together remaining oil and the vinegar; pour over salad.
Toss well until coated.
Add tomatoes and cheese; toss again.

title: angel eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks, cut up finely. Add mayonnaise, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix until smooth.
Fill egg whites with mixture using pastry bag or cookie shooter.
Garnish with olive halves and paprika as desired.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Punch holes with knife in chops. Mix remaining ingredients. Spread marinade with brush over chops. Turn chops and do same to other side using all the sauce.
Refrigerate 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Place chops on platter and garnish with chopped red bell pepper and dill pickles.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Mix flour, brown sugar, oats, walnuts, cinnamon and margarine (softened).
Mix and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown and apples are tender.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: microwave rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered dish and cook 5 to 8 minutes on full power.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes on full power, then let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
I cook mine the longest amount of time.
It may vary with different microwaves.

title: cheese-chicken casserole(serves 8)
directions: Bring water, salt and olive oil to a boil.
Add noodles.
Boil 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, milk, mushrooms and black pepper.
Arrange half of noodles in ungreased 13 1/2 x 8 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with half of soup mixture.
Top with half of cottage cheese and half of chicken.
Sprinkle with half of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with Parmesan and paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: choufleur delight
directions: Separate the cauliflower into florets.
Place these in a large bowl and chill in the refrigerator.
Put the onion, celery leaves, sour cream, caraway seed, salt and Vinaigrette Dressing in a smaller bowl and stir until blended. Add this mixture to the florets and stir in thoroughly.
Line a salad bowl with lettuce leaves before adding the salad.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cajun stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 325° until you can easily pierce with fork (about 1 1/2 hours).
Cut lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving enough of the potatoes to hold shells firmly together.
Whip potatoes with margarine, whipping cream, Cajun Land Cajun seasoning, onions, meat and cheese.
Refill potato shells with mixture.
Reheat at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: round steak with tomato gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Put in large casserole dish.
Top with tomato soup and onion.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
(Do not add water to soup.)
Cover and bake about one hour.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: all fruit punch
directions: Dilute lemonade and 1 can orange juice as directed.
Add the other can of orange juice without diluting.
Add remaining juices and mix well.
Divide between 2 half gallon containers and keep cool until ready to serve.
Pour contents of one container into punch bowl and add ice.
Stir to chill.
Add one bottle of ginger ale and one bottle of soda; add half the strawberries.
Serve. Repeat with remaining ingredients when needed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, cheese, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
Form into a ball and cover with nuts.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: venison jerky
directions: Mix together and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.
Remove meat and dry on paper towels.
Place on cookie sheet in single layer and dry in 200° oven for 6 to 8 hours, or until it feels dry.
Cool and put in airtight jar.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in order listed.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown and pull away from sides of pans.
Let cool for 10 minutes; remove from pans and frost.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until thick.	Add Eagle Brand milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Put vanilla wafers in bottom if 8x11x2 pan and around sides.
Slice bananas and add a layer of bananas and a layer of pudding mix.
Serves 10.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to cream.
Add egg and beat well.
Beat in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add in gradually.
Roll into small balls; place on greased cookie sheet. Flatten balls with fork tines.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip, then fold Cool Whip in. Pour in crusts and refrigerate several hours (at least 2 hours).

title: pasta fagioli
directions: In large pan, simmer crushed tomatoes and white beans.
In a small skillet, add olive oil and saute onions, garlic and 2 hot peppers until tender.
Add paste and saute another 10 minutes. Boil Ditali until almost package time.
Only use enough water to cover when cooked.
Add paste mixture to crushed tomatoes and beans and simmer a while.
Then add Ditali, water and all to sauce and beans.
Simmer 30 minutes and serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Heat cottage cheese and butter to lukewarm.
Combine sugar, onion, dill seed, salt, soda and egg. Combine 3 mixtures.
Add flour and beat well.
Cover and let rise until double (1 hour).
Stir down and put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Put in oven at 350°.
Cook 40 to 50 minutes.
Take out of pan immediately.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with coarse salt.

title: venison jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set overnight in Ziploc bag. Preheat oven to 200°.
Put a layer of aluminum on bottom rack. Place strips of meat over bars on top rack.
Prop oven door open 1 to 2 inches.
Jerky takes 6 to 10 hours to bake.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250 degrees.
Combine cereal and nuts in 13 x 9 pan. Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in a 2-cup microwavable bowl.
Microwave on high 1 1/2 minutes; stir. Microwave on high 30 to 90 seconds more or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over cereal and stir to coat.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool; break into pieces.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Into skillet, place sugar, flour, cocoa, milk, butter and vanilla and cook until thickened.
Add well beaten egg yolks, very rapidly.
Pour into baked pie crust and top with egg whites that have been beaten until peaks stand.
When peaks stand, add 4 tablespoons sugar and cream of tartar and beat again before putting on pie.
Brown in moderate oven.

title: potato spinach casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 400°.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease	a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle coconut on top.	Add dry cake mix.
(Do not mix!)
Sprinkle
the
nuts	and
then
drizzle the melted margarine
over
the
top.	Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Top and core peppers.
Salt inside.
Mix rest of ingredients and stuff into peppers.
Place in crock-pot.
Cover with mix of water, one can of tomato sauce and one beef bouillon.
Place inverted plate on top to keep peppers submerged.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl except vinegar, sugar and oil.
Heat vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add salad oil to mixture; pour over vegetables and marinate.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until completely chilled.
Vegetables will be very crispy.
Thinly round sliced carrots are optional.

title: kat's rice pudding
directions: Warm milk and add rice.
Simmer, covered, until rice is cooked.
Beat eggs and sugar until consistency of syrup.
Mix 3 or 4 tablespoons of hot rice mixture into egg mixture and add to pot. Cook about 1 or 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg, if desired.

title: red clam spaghetti sauce
directions: Good also with onion and/or mushrooms.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix dry mustard and vinegar together well.
Refrigerator overnight.
Next day, beat 3 eggs.
Add to vinegar mixture.
Cook in top of double boiler for 20-25 minutes until thickened.
Put into jars and keep in refrigerator.
(Makes a good gift.)

title: sensibly delicious chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Cream brown sugar, granulated sugar, margarine and vanilla in a large mixer bowl.
Beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonful onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until centers are set.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: country peach tart
directions: Roll pastry on floured surface into 12-inch circle; transfer to ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine flour and Equal; sprinkle over peaches and toss.
Arrange peaches on pastry, leaving a 2-inch border around edge of pastry.
Sprinkle peaches lightly with nutmeg.
Fold edge of pastry in.
Bake tart in preheated 425° oven until crust is browned and fruit is tender, 24 to 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust.
Sprinkle with pecans; refrigerate.

title: blueberry creme pie
directions: Mix together whipped cream, cream cheese and instant pudding. Layer in crust bananas, pudding mix and blueberries.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt sugar; when melted, add water and butter and allow to dissolve.
Scald milk and add to mixture.
Beat egg yolks.
Add brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and cold milk.
Add mixture to hot mixture.
Cook on low heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Cool; pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and cover with meringue. Bake at 325° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef with onions in Dutch oven.
Add taco seasoning, salad dressing mix, beans, chilies, hominy, stewed tomatoes and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Keeps well in freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 3/4 crumbs into a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and chestnuts together (might want to add a little stock from chicken to make custard-like consistency).
Place cubed chicken on top of crumbs in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over and top with remaining crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: spinach cheese stuffing shells
directions: Cook pasta shells in salted water until tender; drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl, except spaghetti sauce.
Stir to mix.
Stuff each pasta shell with mixture; set in baking pan.
When all shells are stuffed, pour spaghetti sauce over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: picnic pickles
directions: Mix vinegar with sugar until dissolved.
Pour over sliced pickles.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts, stirring continuously until it turns a brownish gold. Take from fire, add butter, salt and soda.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: canned green beans
directions: Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Add beans.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.
(Have jars and lids hot.)

title: pie crust
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well with a fork.
Add shortening and mix with fork until ingredients are crumbly.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate and shortening over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat; mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly. Frost with Chocolate Frosting if desired.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth; combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired.
Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread (to soak up the gravy).
Cole slaw is a nice winter accompaniment or serve fresh tomatoes on a bed of lettuce in summer.
Yields 8 servings. Diabetic Exchanges:
One serving equals 3 protein, 1 bread, 2 vegetable, 1/2 fat; also, 311 calories, 660 mg sodium, 103 mg cholesterol, 26 gm carbohydrate, 29 gm protein, 10 gm fat.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar; cut in margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture into bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions (pour off brine).
Drain.
Cook peppers, onions and all other ingredients until it boils.
Time 30 minutes and pack in jars with 2-piece lids.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have an 8-inch square pan ready.
Put flour, granulated sugar, 1/4 cup of the cocoa, baking powder and salt into the ungreased pan.
Stir with a fork to mix well.
Stir in milk and oil until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle brown sugar, the remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and the chocolate chips over the batter.
Pour the hot water evenly over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until surface looks dry, like a brownie.
Cool about 10 minutes, then scoop into serving bowl and top with a scoop of ice cream and a cherry.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Place apples in mixing bowl, add sugar.
Stir, then let stand for 1/2 hour.
Add oil and beaten egg, blend.
Mix dry ingredients and add slowly, stirring good.
Then add vanilla.
Turn into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, dust with xxxx sugar.

title: vegetables kids love
directions: Slice all vegetables in thin slices.
Layer squash, onion and tomatoes in narrow rows, dotting with butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and 1 tablespoon water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then crumbs.
Brown in skillet; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onion, basil, garlic powder and oregano.
Cover.
Cook 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and heat until cheese melts.

title: apple cookies
directions: Grate apple, skin and all.
Work in dry milk, Equal and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: poor man's pound cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients at once.
Beat on medium speed for 10 minutes.
Bake in tube pan for 45 to 55 minutes in a 325° or 350° oven.

title: karen's mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove all bones, then chop.
Blend soups, chili powder and Ro-Tel in blender.
Add onion and blend smooth. Cut cheese into small cubes and add to soup mixture, then add chicken.
Mix. Start with a layer of crushed Doritos in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then add a layer of chicken mixture and then Doritos until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Fill cup half full with mixture.
Add boiling water.
Enjoy!

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cube Velveeta and layer over vegetables.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle over cheese.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugars, milk and margarine to a soft ball.
Remove from the stove and add peanut butter (I like to use extra crunchy) and vanilla.
Stir well. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gloop(craft idea)
directions: Mix glue and 1 1/2 cups warm water in a large bowl.
Add water and Borax mixture slowly (1/3 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon Borax), in 3 parts to the mixture of water and glue.

title: spagetti
directions: First you cook the noodels and add the suace and then add the meat and sezen.
Then eat it!

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a loaf pan.
Pour on an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce over the meat loaf.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in a saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Use wherever barbecue sauce is called for.

title: peanut butter oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Cream butter, peanut butter and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs to creamed mixture.
Gradually stir in dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or less if you want chewy cookies.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut margarine into mixture until mixture resembles corn meal. Stir in caraway seed and raisins.
Set mixture aside.
Mix together milk and vinegar.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: school house cookies(butter cookies)
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Continue beating on low speed, adding flour slowly.
Mix until thoroughly blended.

title: apple cobbler(sugar-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish with vegetable spray.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
In a large bowl with rubber spatula, toss apples, lemon juice, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Arrange in baking dish.
In a medium bowl with fork, combine the flour and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
With pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture over apples. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until crust is golden and apples are tender. Immediately sprinkle lo-cal sweetener over crust.
Makes 9 servings.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Combine well and pour in crust.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix everything together.
Drop small amounts onto cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Dip chicken in melted butter and then roll in dry mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until juices run clear.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Heat shortening; add molasses, sugar and buttermilk.
Cool and add egg (beaten).
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add liquid mixture to make stiff dough.
Divide into 8 even balls.
Press into round cake pans and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Stack with applesauce or apple butter.

title: yankee baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Add thinly sliced onions, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar to drippings.
Mix and simmer 15 minutes.
In bean pot or casserole dish, combine pork and beans with drained Great Northern beans and drained butter beans.
Add onion mixture and bacon; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Put melted butter in baking pan.
Dip chicken in milk.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in pan skin side down.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn and bake 15 minutes.
Add a mixture of the soup and buttermilk; pour over chicken and continue to bake until done and sauce is bubbly.
Sauce is delicious over rice.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix together uncooked.
Put in refrigerator for the next 3 days.
Knead the mixture for 5 minutes each day.
On the fifth day, form into rolls (6 to 8).
Put into oven on a cookie sheet. Bake at 160° for 9 hours.
Turn over after 4 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, 2/3 cup sugar and salt; gradually add milk.	Cook over moderate heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Place small amount of mixture in beaten egg yolks.
Stir and slowly add contents to hot mixture; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add butter, vanilla and 1 cup coconut; cool slightly.
Pour into baked pastry shell; cool.
Cover with meringue made of 3 egg whites, dash of salt and 6 tablespoons sugar (see Marie Ritcher's meringue recipe printed in this book).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on top of meringue. Brown in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden tan.

title: california orange carrots
directions: Combine carrots, salt and water in a saucepan; cook until crisp tender. Drain and return carrots to pan and add orange peel, butter, oranges and onion. Heat through. Serve immediately.

title: fresh shrimp salad
directions: Cut shrimp in half and combine with remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes or more.
Stir before serving. Serve on a bed of lettuce or on a croissant or sandwich roll. Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Roll each chicken breast around 2 times in prepared stuffing.
Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over chicken rolls.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat in double boiler.
Serve in chafing dish with assorted crackers.

title: chocolate chip toffee bars(skor bars)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl, stir flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the chips and nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour Eagle Brand over hot crust.
Top with 1 1/2 cups toffee bits.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture and remaining chocolate chips over top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with remaining toffee bits while hot.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars. These bars freeze well.

title: german springerle cookies
directions: Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl on high until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar, 1/4 cup at a time.
Continue beating until mixture is very thick and pale.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and lemon peel to egg mixture.
Let rest in refrigerator at least 2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg, water, and vanilla.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: In sequence listed, combine spinach, flour, eggs, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, salt and margarine.
Pour mixture into buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in bottom of dish.
Mix soup and cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix chicken broth and margarine together; mix with stuffing mix.
Spoon on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until brown.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients in large skillet and simmer until beef is tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in order, except flour.
Add the flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 10 minutes.

title: head cheese
directions: Scald and scrape pig's head.
Cook pig head in a large kettle until meat falls off the bone.
Reserve the broth or juice.
Finely cut up meat.
Dissolve head meat juice, vinegar, sugar and gelatin in a saucepan.
Add salt, pepper and mixed spice to taste.
Simmer until thoroughly hot.
Place cut up meat in a bread loaf pan.
Pour mixture over the meat and let stand until it is cool.
Wrap and freeze.
Thaw and slice to eat like luncheon meat.

title: hearty baked macaroni
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato puree, water, Italian seasonings and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top mixed with some grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 2 to 3 teaspoons with cup of boiling water.
Sit back and enjoy.

title: shrimp stuffed celery
directions: Combine shrimp, mayonnaise, lemon juice, parsley, onion, pineapple, walnuts, salt and hot pepper sauce; mix well.
Stuff celery stalks.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 cups shrimp mixture.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Measure water into 2-cup glass measure.
Gradually stir in dry milk powder until smooth.
Microwave on High for 50 to 60 seconds or until milk is steaming hot.
Stir in sugar until dissolved. Allow to cool before using.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pan.
Top with ketchup and bake 25 minutes in microwave.
Top with Saran Wrap while cooking.

title: seasoned potatoes(can be made in oven, over campfire or on the grill)
directions: Slice or dice potatoes with or without skins on.
Amount depends on how many people or how big of baking dish you're using. Sprinkle all-purpose seasoned salt and dried or fresh onions over potatoes and top with some teaspoons of butter.
If using a baking dish, do two layers of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until soft.
Also, they make great potatoes for cookouts, on grill or over campfire.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Brown chicken breast under the broiler.
Remove from pan.
Use same pan to mix the remaining ingredients.
Place chicken breast on top of mixture and cover with foil and bake (large pan) at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Cook rice; refrigerate.
Boil shrimp in salt water for 10 minutes.
Saute vegetables in margarine until tender.
Add shrimp and rice.
Mix well.
Add soy sauce to taste.

title: ginger and water chestnut dip for veggies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight or 8 hours.
Yields 3 cups.
Serve with veggies.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan. Stir in flour and chili powder. Cook for 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Makes 3 cups.

title: never fail corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat oil in skillet or 8 or 9-inch pan. Also makes Texas-sized muffins.
Combine dry ingredients.
Melt oleo, add milk and eggs.
Add to dry mixture.
Mix until blended. Pour into baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on top.
I start checking at 15 minutes.
Is done when brown on top.

title: heavenly angel biscuits
directions: Stir flour, baking soda and sugar together.
Cut in shortening. Add yeast to warm milk.
Stir and add dry ingredients.
Roll out and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with the mix of oatmeal, cake mix and nuts.
Pour melted oleo on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: "our party" ritz crackers
directions: Spread peanut butter on about 3 dozen Ritz crackers and top each with another Ritz cracker.
In top of double boiler, melt 3 tablespoons Crisco.
Add white chocolate and stir until melted. Drop Ritz sandwiches, one at a time, into melted chocolate, using a spoon to turn and coat.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder, soda and dry milk on a piece of paper or in mixing bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix shortening, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Mix water, vinegar and bananas together.
Gradually add dry ingredients to egg mixture, alternately adding the banana mixture.
Quickly, but thoroughly, stir in nuts.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread leaves side of pan.

title: zucchini tomato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of sliced tomatoes, onions, zucchini and cheese, ending with cheese on top layer. Bake at 350° in a covered casserole 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 15 minutes to brown cheese (will be very juicy).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to tender.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Saute celery and onion to tender.
Remove from heat and add cheese, soup and water, mixing until blended.

title: baked snapper
directions: Put all ingredients except fish in a large skillet and cook until tender.
Place fish in a baking pan and add a little extra olive oil over the fish, then pour the prepared ingredients over top of the fish.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain off excess fat.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles and place in ungreased pizza pan. Press over the bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Seal the perforations.
Spread sausage over crust.
Pat the potatoes dry and sprinkle over sausage.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
In bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Arrange onion in bottom of casserole dish.
Put pork chops on top of onion.
Pour soup on top of pork chops.
Put a good layer of Tater Tots on top of soup.
Put grated cheese on top.
Cover casserole with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: squash delight
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Mix well.
Place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Simmer onion, water, chicken bouillon, salt and potatoes until potatoes are partially tender.
Add broccoli and simmer until soft.
Add milk and Velveeta and heat until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Don't use mixer.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until middle drops.
Cut in squares.

title: glorified pound cake
directions: Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs until smooth.
Add flour and salt.
Then add vanilla extract, almond extract and lemon juice.

title: symphonic sundae sauce
directions: Combine Jell-O pudding, sugar and water in saucepan, blending well.
Place over low heat and cook until all sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture comes to a full boil. Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Serve over ice cream.
Makes 1 cup.

title: dottie's apple butter
directions: Place all these ingredients in a large roasting pan (turkey size).
Stir until well mixed.
Bake 3 or 4 times at 300°, until as dark and thick as desired.
Stir occasionally while cooking. Pour into jars and seal or can be frozen.
This amount makes 12 to 15 pints.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use any fruits you desire.
Mix in bowl and serve with nuts, mayo or alone.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until the dry ingredients are moist; do not overmix.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Best if removed from tin immediately.
I use cupcake papers and then no need to grease muffin tins.
Also easy to remove from pan.

title: clam filled lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine reserved clam liquid and spaghetti sauce.
Set aside 1 cup sauce.
Spoon remainder equally into bottom of baking dish.
In a medium bowl, combine calms, Ricotta, Parmesan, egg and parsley; mix well.
Spread equal portions on lasagna strips; roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam-side down in pan.
Top with remaining sauce and cover.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until hot.
Serve with Parmesan cheese sprinkled over top.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Place all ingredients in an airtight container and shake well.
Mix 2 to 3 tablespoons of chocolate in cup of water or milk and heat well to dissolve the mix.

title: quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend margarine, syrup, peanut butter and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar gradually.
Knead on waxed paper then put in 9 x 13-inch pan and cut in squares.

title: devil's food marshmallow cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix in 2 (9 inch) round cake pans as directed on package, and let cool completely.
Coarsely chop 10 of the cookies.
Add 2 cups of the whipped topping in large bowl along with 1 1/2 cups of the marshmallows; stir gently until well blended.
Place on cake layer on serving dish, spread with whipped topping mixture.
Cover with second cake layer.
Frost top with remaining 1 cup whipped topping.
Refrigerate until read to serve. Garnish with remaining 10 cookies and 1 cup of marshmallows just before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and parsley.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Place tomatoes in blender and blend on high speed for 30 seconds or until chopped.
Add to onion mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold in the floured fruits and nuts.
Makes 3 medium loaves.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, egg and applesauce.
Sift flour and soda and add cinnamon, allspice, cloves, salt, lemon juice and orange juice.
Add flour, raisins, nuts and vanilla and pour into 2 cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Save the chicken broth to add later, if needed.

title: arroz con higaditos de pollo(rice with chicken livers)
directions: Saute livers in butter, salt and pepper until tender.
Chop, set aside; keep warm.
In heavy skillet, heat oil and add onion. When clear, add rice and saute.
Stir until grains are completely coated with oil and begin to turn yellow.
Mix broth, tomato sauce and mustard.
Add slowly to rice, add parsley. Cover well and simmer until broth is almost gone.
Add chicken livers.
Blend well.
Cover and simmer until rice is cooked.

title: "apple cake"
directions: Grease pan.
Beat first 4 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 9 x 15-inch cake pan; set aside.
Cream together shortening, sugar and salt.
Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Add flour, eggs and spices alternating with milk; mix well.
Fold in apples.
Spoon into prepared pan and spread with topping.

title: healthy hobo potato
directions: Chop vegetables into about 5 large pieces each.
Place the vegetables into the shape of the potato on a piece of foil, alternating vegetables.
