Place Spike seasoning on each piece or place on top.
Finally, wrap in aluminum foil and bake for about 1 hour at 350° to 370°.

title: potato sauerkraut soup
directions: In a 4-quart electric crock-pot, stir together first 13 ingredients.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
If necessary, skim off fat before serving.
Sprinkle each serving with bacon and eggs.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together. Put in fridge for an hour or 2 before serving.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add to peaches and toss lightly.
Turn into pie shell.
Pour cream over top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: pinch me cake
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip in sugar and cinnamon. Place in angel food pan.
Melt sugar and butter; pour over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix yeast, water, sugar and salt.
(If it starts to get foamy, the yeast is good.)
Add oil and flour.
Mix.
Let rise.
Add toppings you like.

title: pan liner
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Store in covered container in your refrigerator.
Use to grease all your cake pans.
Saves having to grease and flour pans.
Cakes come out beautifully.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.

Add oil and vanilla. Sift together and add the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add the apples and nuts and mix enough to combine. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly in a baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients, except chicken, and pour over rice.
Pepper chicken and place on top of rice.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil last 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: frog eyed salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and one-half teaspoon of the salt. Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring, until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Bring water, remaining 2 teaspoons salt and oil to boil.
Add soup pasta.
Cook at rolling boil until soup pasta is done.
Drain soup pasta; rinse with water and drain again and cool to room temperature.
Combine egg mixture and soup pasta. Mix lightly, but
thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Refrigerate until chilled in airtight container. Salad may be refrigerated for as long as a week in airtight container.
It also may be frozen, though freezing somewhat alters the texture.
Makes 25 servings.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Cool completely.
Add the orange, lemon and pineapple juices.
Mash bananas in blender and add along with cake color.
Freeze; this keeps up to 4 months. Thaw slightly and add Sprite.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend at high speed in blender for 30 seconds. Make sure cubes are broken up in small pieces.

title: broccoli-ramen salad
directions: *About 1/2 cup each.

title: cornflake kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until just stiff enough to hold moist peaks, then add sugar gradually, about 1 heaping tablespoon at a time.
Continue to beat after each addition, until whites are very stiff.
Mix in nuts, using a fork; then fold in the cornflakes. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased unglazed brown paper on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from paper to cake racks immediately.
Makes about 3 dozen kisses.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients together, reserving 1 cup pecans. Chill well. Shape into ball and cover with remaining pecans.

title: holiday punch
directions: Boil water in a large pot with sugar until sugar dissolves. Add cranberry juice, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Allow to cool and strain.
Add lemon juice, orange juice, pineapple juice and ginger ale.
Chill.
Can be spiked with spiced rum.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk together.
Spoon into pie crust.
Slice bananas over cream cheese mixture.
Drain pineapple and spread pineapple over bananas and spread Cool Whip over top.
Put cherries and chopped pecans on top.

title: apple praline cheesecake
directions: Melt butter in a small saucepan or in a microwavable bowl in the microwave.
Stir in crumbs and sugar until thoroughly blended. Press into the bottom of a 9-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: oreo cookie balls
directions: Using a blender or rolling pin, crumb Oreo cookies finely. Place into a large bowl.
Cut cream cheese until fully incorporated in cookies crumbs.
Place blended mixture in refrigerator for at least one hour.
Roll cookie balls into desired size.
Melt either, milk, white, dark chocolate in microwave and dip one ball at a time to coat using two spoons.
Place onto waxed paper on cookie sheet and place back into refrigerator until hardened.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except nutmeg into buttered 8 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stir twice the first hour, then stir a few times during rest of cooking to stir in crust.
Let crust form for the last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: spoon bread
directions: Slowly add corn meal to the boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add butter and salt and cool to lukewarm, then add eggs and milk and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased casserole and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Spoon out while piping hot and butter.
Yields 8 servings.

title: yum yums
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine. Cool. Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and add sugar and flour.
Stir until mixed well, but do not beat.
Fill paper muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry nut filling
directions: Combine sugar, egg yolks and milk.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Cool, then add other ingredients. Use over yellow mixture.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Up to 1 week ahead:
In double boiler, over hot, not boiling water, heat chocolate pieces and shortening until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth, stirring frequently.
Meanwhile, spray large cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
When chocolate is melted, pat cherries dry with paper towels.
Hold 1 cherry by the stem and dip into chocolate mixture to coat completely.
Shake off excess chocolate; place on cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining cherries.

title: irish cream liqueur
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender. Will keep several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil the oleo, water and cocoa; add this to flour mixture while hot.
Mix well. Pour into greased 11 x 17 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable
directions: Lay rolls flat and crimp edges enough to hold the filling. Cook rolls by directions. Let cool, then mix together 1/2 cup each tomatoes, carrots, green onions, cucumbers, bell peppers, broccoli and celery. Sprinkle over rolls. Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: smoked sausage spanish rice
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine all ingredients, except rice, in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, cover and turn down heat.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir in rice, remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: very best gazpacho
directions: Heat bouillon cubes in the tomato juice until they are dissolved.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except croutons and lime slices.
Chill at least 12 hours.
Turn into serving bowls and garnish each with seasoned croutons and a thin slice of fresh lime. Serves 8 to 10.

title: tomato cheese casserole
directions: Heat butter with onion.
Add tomatoes.
Heat until boiling, then add Swiss cheese.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Add salt, pepper and croutons.
Put in casserole dish and top with more croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nana's savoy cabbage
directions: Clean cabbage and let soak in cold water.
In a pot, place 3 cups of water, oil, garlic and parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Add the cabbage.
When cabbage is half cooked (15 minutes), add potatoes, frying pepper and salt and pepper.
Add water, if needed.
Cover and let cook over medium heat until cabbage is soft.

title: magic marshmallow puffs
directions: Melt margarine; dip marshmallows in melted margarine.
Roll in cinnamon sugar.
Wrap in crescent roll.
Seal well.
Dip top in melted margarine and place in muffin pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Remove from oven and frost with confectioners sugar icing while hot.
Be sure to have aluminum foil under muffin pan because some of the marshmallows will cook out and make a mess in your oven.
Delicious served hot.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: mix jello and hot water.
Add cream cheese and mix until there are no lumps.
Add mayonnaise and sugar and mix until mayonnaise is melted.
Add pineapple and nuts and stir.
Prepare dream whip according to directions on package and stir into jello mixture.
Chill till set.
Stir several times so nuts will not float.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Saute all in oil for approximately 20 minutes.
Start on high; as soon as liquid begins to boil, reduce to low.

title: southern chicken pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust.
Melt butter; add flour and stir until light brown, about 2 minutes).
Stir in broth.
Stir until thick. Slowly add milk stirring.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Cook until quite thick, about 5 minutes.
Add chicken and Veg-All and pour in crust.
Seal.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: macaroni salad veronique
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Combine macaroni, ham, grapes and onions; add dressing.
Toss lightly until well coated.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Yield:
4 to 6 meals.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Pour off excess grease.
Drain beans; mix with hamburger, sliced tomatoes, cheese, lettuce and olives. Mix with hamburger and beans.
Just before serving, add crushed Fritos.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Flatten with a fork that has been dipped in cold water. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 325°.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid.
Place carrots in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and reserved liquid. Spread over carrots.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french apple pie
directions: Mix together tapioca, salt, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and apples.
Fill pie shell with apple mixture; dot with butter.
Cut slits in top of crust to permit escape of steam.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 55 minutes or until syrup boils with heavy bubbles that don't burst.
Cool and frost top with thin confectioners sugar icing.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: leslie's jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Sift flour with salt and spices.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with buttermilk and rest of ingredients except the eggs.
Beat well and add the eggs last.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour and alum together.
In saucepan heat water, oil and food coloring to boil.
Stir liquids into dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add next four ingredients.
Add flour.
Stir in carrots.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli milanese
directions: In small baking dish, cover broccoli with egg. Add crumbs and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Delicious!

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Mix the brown sugar, flavoring, 1/2 cup white sugar and sliced peaches together; set aside.
Make batter of the flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt, melted butter and milk.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Cover with peach mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
If it browns too fast, reduce heat to 325°.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: momma's mexican cream cheese dip
directions: Mix well and enjoy!

title: raspberry almond bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil. Lightly grease foil.
Mix flour, oats and sugar in large bowl.
Cut oleo into mixture until you have coarse crumbs.
Stir in extract until well blended.
Reserve about 1 cup oat mixture.
Press remainder evenly in bottom of pan.
Spread preserves on top, about 1/2 inch from edges.
Mix almonds with reserved oat mixture. Sprinkle over preserves, then press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges are golden.
Cool in pan on rack.
Lift foil by ends to cutting board.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: summer cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into 8-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°, also preheat cookie sheet that will hold pie.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract. Gradually add scalded milk.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked). Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool pie on rack 15 to 30 minutes, then chill in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray three cake tins with Pam; set aside.
Mix all ingredients together (mixer will cut up orange slices).
Pour into cake tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with frosting.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Skin and bone chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Dip the tortillas into broth and layer in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine the chicken with green pepper, onion and green chilies.
Toss lightly to mix.
Spread a layer of chicken mixture over the tortillas.
Sprinkle with chili powder, repeat until all is used.
Combine soup with a can of broth; blend until smooth. Pour soup mixture over all and bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour or until heated through or bubbly.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in shortening until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and next 5 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water.
Stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
(Serves 6.)

title: sauce for coneys
directions: Brown ground chuck, tomato puree and chili powder well.
Add kidney beans and paprika; mash (I use a potato masher).
It makes a lot.
I freeze some for later.

title: banana slush
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add frozen concentrate, then mashed bananas.
Freeze solid.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer; thaw until slushy.
Add 1 quart lemon-lime, Sprite or 7-Up.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: world war ii raisin squares
directions: Adjust a rack one-third up from the bottom of the oven and preheat the oven to 375°.
Line a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan as follows: Turn the pan over; cover it with a 12-inch square of aluminum foil.
Press down the sides and corners of the foil to shape it, then remove the foil.
Turn the pan over again; place the foil in the pan, and press it into place.
To butter the foil, place a piece of butter in the pan and place it in the oven to melt, then spread it over the bottom and sides with a pastry brush or crumbled wax paper.
Set aside.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Add all ingredients.
Stir and bring to a boil for 1 minute. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corned beef omelet
directions: Beat together eggs and milk with salt.
Tear up corned beef, Cheddar cheese and onion.
Stir all together and pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all but the last 2 ingredients.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with buttered crumbs (and almonds, if desired).
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes, until bubbly.
Frozen or canned peas may be added.
Serves 6.

title: eileen's chicken
directions: Clean chicken; set aside.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, empty the can of cream of celery soup and add 1 1/2 cans of water plus salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add the stuffing mix; stir until the stuffing is even in the dish.
Add only the heads of the broccoli to the mixture.
Add the chicken to the dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Remove the dish; sprinkle the grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Return to the oven for 10 minutes, or until the cheese has melted.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: *If using can fruits, use juice and fruits (use all).
You may use peaches, apples, blueberries, etc.

title: chocolate chip picnic bars
directions: Beat shortening and sugars together until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.

title: tomato salad
directions: Arrange tomatoes and cheese on platter.
Mix basil and olive oil and pour over tomatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Serves six.

title: lemon sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix first 3 ingredients.
Stir in water and cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot on puddings or breads.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an average size dish (9 x 12-inch).
Add sweet milk, flour and sugar.
Mix these 3 ingredients thoroughly, and add to melted butter.
Add fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for approximately 40 minutes or until browning is noted.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large plastic bowl.
Add oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Cover.
Store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full and bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes lots!
Will keep approximately 6 weeks.

title: pecan brittle(microwave)
directions: Combine nuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart bowl. Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring twice. Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add soda until foamy and spread quickly on greased cookie sheet.
(Some microwaves cook faster.
You may have to adjust cooking time.)

title: easy brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add butter and melted chocolate. Add flour, salt and vanilla; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: jim bennett's spaghetti
directions: Empty Lawry's package into saucepan.
Add tomatoes, olives, salad oil and stir thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes, stirring often.
Brown ground beef while stirring in all of the seasonings, onion and bell pepper.

title: sparkling berry salad
directions: Stir boiling cranberry juice into gelatin in large bowl, at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved. Stir in cold seltzer, liqueur and lemon juice. Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened. Stir in 2 cups of the berries. Spoon into 5 cups. Refrigerate four hours or until firm. Unmold. Top with remaining 1 cup berries.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Saute celery and onions. Add meat and brown, then add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 1 hour.

title: oatmeal buttermilk pancakes
directions: The night before, mix oats and buttermilk and refrigerate.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Shake flour into cooking bag.
Pat dry chicken; place in bag. Pour in barbecue sauce.
Turn bag to coat meat with sauce.
Close bag and place in pan at least 2 inches deep.
Make six 1/2-inch slits in top of bag.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a large rectangular casserole (9 x 14-inches), make first layer of 8 slices bread, side by side.
In next layer, place half ham pieces.
Next layer 8 slices American cheese, then another layer of bread, ham and Swiss cheese.
Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking, sprinkle with buttered crumbs (mix 3 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/2 cup melted butter).
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Wash cabbage; cut in eighths (big chunks).
Add all ingredients, except meat.
When about 1/2 done (wilting good), add your favorite meat.
Add enough water to just keep moist so it doesn't stick or rush them.

title: asparagus with shrimp sauce
directions: Drain half of juice from asparagus.
Salt to taste; set aside. Combine sour cream and cream of shrimp soup in double boiler. Heat, stirring constantly, until well blended and hot.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Heat asparagus until hot. To serve, pour shrimp sauce over asparagus.

title: breakfast lasagna
directions: Layer one half of the bread, ham and cheese in the order given in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat to make a second layer.
In blender, put milk, eggs, onion salt and mustard.
Blend 2 minutes and pour over layers.
Melt butter in pan, remove from heat and add cornflakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 1/2 hours before serving.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yorkshire sausage
directions: Brown sausage in 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Do not drain. Keep hot.
In bowl, beat 2 minutes.
Add flour, milk and salt. Beat until smooth.
Stir in chives.
Pour over sausage.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Lower oven to 350°.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt with a wire whisk.
Set aside.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients.
Ice with mayonnaise and sugar (mixed together).
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Don't stir from 12 to 24 hours.
Serve immediately.

title: quiche
directions: Beat eggs and fold in cream.
Place bacon and cheese on bottom of prepared pie shell.
Pour egg and cream mixture over bacon and cheese.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: emily's flank steak barbecue
directions: Mix salt, oregano, oil and vinegar and pour over meat.
Place meat on prepared grill 4 inches from hot coals.
Cook 5 minutes on each side, basting with tomato sauce.
To serve, cut steak diagonally across the grain.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, peppers, salt and sliced onions.
Kiver wid watah 'n let stand in the ice box all nite.

title: tomato-basil squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Using lightly floured roller, roll out pizza crust on 12 x 15 in. rectangle baking stone to within 1 inch of edge of stone.
Sprinkle crust with 1 cup of the mozzarella cheese; set aside.
In 1 qt. bowl combine the remaining 1 cup mozzarella cheese, parmesan, basil and mayo; mix well. Arrange the thinly sliced tomatoes in single layer over mozzarella cheese on crust.
Place mozzarella cheese mixture over tomatoes; spread to cover evenly.
Bake 15-20 min. or until top is golden brown and bubbly.
Serve warm.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: tossed salad dressing
directions: Mix together in blender until well blended.
Store in refrigerator.

title: german wiener schnitzel
directions: With meat mallet pound cutlets to 1/8-inch thickness.
In pie plate, beat eggs, salt and pepper.
On wax paper, place flour on one sheet and bread crumbs on another.
Coat veal in flour, dip in eggs, then coat with bread crumbs.
In skillet (over medium heat), melt 1/4 cup of the butter or margarine.
Cook the cutlets, a few slices at a time, 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Add other 1/4 cup of butter or margarine as needed.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: lazy wife cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a 9 x 9-inch ungreased cake pan. Mix them with a fork.
Make 3 holes in this mixture.
Into one put the vanilla, into the next the oil and into the third the vinegar.
Pour cold water over all of this.
Mix these ingredients with a fork, but do not beat them.
Bake the batter at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Melt margarine, mix with cracker crumbs and sugar. Put into bottom of 8 inch square pyrex dish and pat down with spatula.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips or serving size pieces.
Brown lightly in a hot skillet in a small amount of oil.
Remove meat; add mixture of catsup, flour, bouillon, soy sauce and water to skillet. Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Return meat to skillet; cover and cook over gentle heat until steak is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Add salt, pepper, onion slices, mushrooms and peppers.
Cover and steam until vegetables are just tender.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Chop pecans and mix with coconut.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach salad with cooked dressing
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft, blend in flour and salt.
Add water, lemon juice, horseradish and Worcestershire.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Dice 1 of eggs and stir into dressing.
Pour dressing over spinach that has been washed and torn into small pieces and is in a bowl.
Toss lightly.
Garnish with egg and crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together, add Crisco and mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, mix 1/2 cup water, egg and vinegar. Combine the 2 mixtures until moistened.
Divide into 5 balls; chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 5 (9-inch) crusts.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in deep kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery.
Bring to a boil; cover tightly.
Reduce heat; simmer for 1 hour.
Remove from heat; strain broth. Refrigerate chicken and broth at once.
When chicken is cool, remove from bones.
Discard skin.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: pudding cups
directions: Make pudding according to directions on box.
Crush the Oreo cookies; put into a bowl.

title: mexican bean salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let marinate overnight in refrigerator.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix garlic powder, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Cook noodles in salt water; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs, then add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper.
Layer 1/2 of each: noodles, cheese filling, meat and repeat.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fisherman's tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients well and chill.
Makes 2 cups of sauce.

title: mushroom burgers
directions: Prepare noodles; set aside.
Fry hamburger patties; drain grease.
Add mushroom soup and milk to patties and stir until smooth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with noodles.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook rice.
Combine beef, rice, tomato soup and mushroom soup.
Add the seasonings.
Mix; let sit for 5 minutes.
Serve with bread and butter.
Enjoy!

title: spicy pan-fried catfish
directions: Combine corn meal and seasonings.
Roll fish in seasoned meal. Shake off excess meal and place in a single layer in hot oil in a 12-inch frypan.
Fry at moderate heat until well browned, turning to brown both sides, about 4 minutes on each side.
Remove from pan with a slotted spatula and drain on paper towel. Garnish with lemon wedges and serve with slaw and corn bread or hush puppies. Serves 6.

title: english toffee
directions: In a saucepan, combine butter, sugar and almonds; cook until it reaches 300° on candy thermometer (or hard crack stage).
Spread into a large cookie sheet and let cool in dry place for 3 to 4 hours.
Note:
Do not cool in refrigerator as it will cause the candy to become soft.
Crack randomly with an ice cream scoop.
Do not remove from pan yet.

title: old indian corn cakes
directions: Mix corn meal, baking powder and salt; add enough buttermilk to mix well.
Batter should be thick to drop on hot oiled skillet. Fry like pancakes.
Brown on both sides.
This goes well with any type of greens, such as mustard, turnip or spinach.

title: best beer rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend together all except chips and nuts with mixer.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop small balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon frosting
directions: Cook all ingredients over double boiler until thick.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: Mix ingredients and allow to sit for 1 hour before using. Keep refrigerated.

title: stir-fried carrots and mushrooms
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet until bubbly; add carrots, mushrooms and onions.
Cook and stir about 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper. Yields 6 servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Blend flour into the shortening from which the meat was removed.
Add catsup, water, soy sauce, pepper, bouillon cube, minced garlic and chopped onion.
Bring to a boil, lower heat to simmer for 20 minutes.
Drop meat into sauce and cook only until tender.

title: zucchini, onion and carrot saute
directions: Wash zucchini, but do not peel.
Cut into thin slices.
Put into a 10-inch skillet.
Add carrots, onions, salt, black pepper and basil.
Pour olive oil over top; stir gently until well mixed with vegetables.
Over medium heat, saute vegetables for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover vegetables; cook 5 minutes longer.
Remove cover; stir and cook about 10 more minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In saucepan, melt margarine over low heat; blend in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add Parmesan cheese, lemon juice and dill weed.
Stir in broccoli and tuna.
Pour into casserole and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Arrange biscuits around edge of hot casserole and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: *chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Bring milk to scalding in a double boiler; add shaved chocolate to melt.
Then add milk mixture gradually to dry ingredients and stir constantly until filling thickens.
To this, add beaten egg yolks and butter or margarine. Continue to cook for 5 more minutes.
Add vanilla and cool.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell and cover with meringue.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough, but do not let it rise.
Roll out to approximately 8 1/2 x 11-inch.
Lightly sprinkle with olive oil. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Layer with thinly sliced pepperoni, making sure to completely cover the dough.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese over pepperoni.
Lightly sprinkle with olive oil.
Next, sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Sprinkle with more grated Parmesan cheese.
Now roll the dough into a loaf.
Roll from the narrow end, rolling firmly to ensure the pepperoni and cheese stay inside the dough.
Seal the ends firmly and place on a foil-lined cookie sheet with the seal down.
The bread needs to rise for a couple of hours, covered with a sheet of waxed paper or dish towel.
Before baking, brush the top of the loaf with an egg white.
Bake the length of time and at the temperature stated on the frozen bread dough wrapper.
Once this is baked and cooled, it may be refrozen if properly wrapped.
Just thaw and reheat wrapped in foil.
This makes a delicious entree served with a salad or as a hot appetizer.

title: chocolate quad
directions: Cut butter into flour with a pastry blender or fork until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in pecans.
Press mixture onto bottom of a 13x9 inch pan.
Bake at 350°F for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 1 cup whipped topping at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Spread mixture over prepared crust.
Whisk together pudding mix and milk for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Chill 10 minutes.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding mixture.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour. Cut into squares.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: my favorite noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Rinse and set aside.
Brown onions, celery, peppers and beef in butter. Stir.
Add salt, pepper and cooked noodles.
Blend the condensed soups with 3/4 can of water and add to the mixture.
Bake in greased baking dish in 350 °oven for about 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until thick.
Gradually add the liquors, stirring constantly.
Blend in the cream and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and peaks are formed.
Gently fold into eggnog.
Turn into punch bowl, cover and chill.
To serve, ladle eggnog into punch cups and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a blender, except ice cubes, and blend for 4 seconds.
Then, add ice cubes, one at a time, to the blender and blend them.
Then, enjoy!
Makes 5 servings.

title: ranch snack mix
directions: In a very large bowl, combine pretzels, Bugels, cashews and crackers.
Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Toss gently.
Drizzle with oil.
Toss until well coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Dip sliced eggplants in egg.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry. In 9 x 13-inch dish, layer eggplants with cheeses, cover with sauce and continue to layer until dish is full.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Put 1 cup sugar over cherries.
Let stand until you make the batter.
Cream together egg, butter and sugar; add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased baking dish, then pour cherries on top of batter.
Pour 3/4 cup boiling water over all.
Do not stir at all.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of peach Jell-O with 2 cups of hot water. Add 2 cups of cold water.
Let congeal a little.
Add drained pineapple and miniature marshmallows.
Let congeal.

title: icing for jam cake
directions: Combine sugar with flour.
Add milk and butter.
Cook until thick; add coconut and nuts.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: A good way to use up leftover ham, making a hearty dish out of just a little meat.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Add to egg, sugar and butter mixture.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Bake until done, about 35 minutes.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; add to dry ingredients and pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm and light brown.

title: savory cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and place in shallow greased baking dish. Mix dry ingredients and add cream; pour cabbage. Top with bacon. Cook uncovered at 450° until done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; drain and rinse.
Mix in soup, cheese and green beans.
Cook until cheese is melted and mixed well.
Pour into casserole dish; place Tater Tots on top and cook in oven at 350° until Tater Tots are brown.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix all together but don't overmix.
Batter may be lumpy. Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Yields 12.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Put in colander cucumber and onion and drain 2 hours.
Mix turmeric, salt, celery seed, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add cucumbers and onion.
Boil 20 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: browning pudding
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and shortening; mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Boil vinegar and spices, then add cucumber slices and heat slightly.
Put in clean jars and seal.
Do not cook slices too long or they will not be crisp.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually.
Continue to beat until it thickens.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding flour until you get the consistency to roll out.
Then roll out on floured counter to about 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Then cut in strips about 1/2 inch wide.
Let dry for at least 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Combine cottage cheese, onion powder, salt, eggs, Cheddar cheese and broccoli in large bowl.

When mixed well, pour into 9 x 12 baking dish. Make topping of melted butter and crumbs. Sprinkle on top of broccoli mix. Bake at 350° for one (1) hour or until knife inserted comes out clean. Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: potluck dinner
directions: Get big pan and cut Polish sausage into bite size pieces, then peel potatoes and cut into bite size pieces.
Drain 2 cans green beans and put all into pan.
Your whole meal will be done in 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and honey until light.
Add eggs, banana pulp, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, softened in water; add egg. Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough. Beat vigorously; cover and let rise until doubled in bulk. Turn out on floured surface and cut with round biscuit cutter. Put in greased pan and turn top 3/4 the way down, then roll and press lightly. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: early bird coffee cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Cut in sugar and shortening until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Stir in milk and eggs just until all flour is moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
9 to 12 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour string beans
directions: Brown bacon in pot you will use to cook the beans.
Remove and save.
Put onion in pan with bacon drippings; use liquid from 1 can of beans and drain other can.
Add brown sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil, then add beans and cook on low heat at least 30 minutes.
Add crumbled bacon and serve.

title: rich basic cakedallas, texas
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until fluffy.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper in skillet.
Crumble ground beef and brown at 350° (medium heat) for 10 minutes; stir.
Drain grease and turn down heat to 250° (medium/low).
Add all the noodles and dried chives, onion bits and water.
Cook at 250° for 10 to 15 minutes until noodles are tender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add the other ingredients, except nuts.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and spread Marshmallow Creme on top.
Cool and cover with icing.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Place 2 cups boiling water in pan.
Add jello and stir until jello is dissolved.
Add ginger ale and lemon juice.
Allow to set until it's about half set up.
Add apple, celery, nuts and pineapple.
Stir well.
Pour in pan, 9 x 13-inch, and chill until firm.

title: dad's favorite potato soup
directions: Place chopped celery, onion, potatoes, water and bouillon cubes in pressure cooker and cook until tender (about 20 minutes). Mash with potato masher until smooth.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
Heat to piping hot.
Do not allow to boil.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.
Serves 4.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in an ungreased oblong pan at 350° until done.

title: holiday peas
directions: Combine peas, cucumber, water, tarragon and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain.
Combine sour cream, mayo and lemon juice.
Warm over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir vegetables into sauce and serve at once.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Beat 2 egg whites until foamy; add pinch of salt.
Gradually add sugar while beating until real stiff, until it stands in peaks.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet well.
Drop cookie batter by spoonfuls onto greased foil.
Place in heated oven; turn oven off.
Leave in oven 5 hours or overnight.

title: fresh apple squares
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil together until well blended.
Stir together dry ingredients and add gradually.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool, dust with confectioners sugar and serve.
